title: "reese's peanut butter cups"
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup peanut butter, crackers and sugar and pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch deep pan.
Melt chocolate chips along with 1 cup peanut butter and pour over top mixture.
Let it set until top mixture is firm (in refrigerator).

title: mocha torte
directions: Beat
egg
whites until stiff.	Add vinegar.
Gradually add sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.

Fold in chopped nuts and Ritz crackers.	Spread in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.	Remove from oven and cool. To whipped cream, add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, instant coffee and powdered sugar.
Whip
until stiff.	Spread over cooled torte shell.
Chill in refrigerator and add chocolate morsels before serving.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops and drain off fat.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Peel and slice potatoes (round) and place on top of pork chops.
Add small amount of milk to mushroom soup and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in a slow cooker on low all day (about 6 to 8 hours).
Take a few of the beans out and mash them; add to the other beans to thicken gravy.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a skillet cook and stir meat and onion in butter until browned.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
May be served over noodles if desired.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and rice (from box) in bacon drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to boil, then reduce to simmer.

title: cookies and cream cheesecake
directions: *These cookies (24) should be chocolate cream filled cookies and be chopped as fine as can be done.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Place eggplant in a colander and sprinkle with coarse salt. Let stand for 1 hour.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute eggplant until almost tender.
Add oil as needed.
Heat the remaining 1/4 cup oil in same skillet over low heat.
Add onions, garlic and green peppers and saute just until softened, about 10 minutes.
Add to the casserole with oil.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Mix shortening, flour, water, vanilla and pecans.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°. Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: foolproof pie crust(makes 3 crusts)
directions: Blend flour and Crisco shortening.
Add blended in egg, cold water, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Mix into flour.
Divide into 3 balls.
Should be soft dough.
If needed, add few drops of water. Roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Bake at 350° for pie shell or if fruit pies, bake at 350° until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend butter into syrup; stir in peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well until creamy.
Stir in 10x sugar.
Turn candy onto pastry board; knead until blended and smooth.
Add nuts gradually, pressing and kneading into dough.
Press candy into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into squares. Yield:
2 pounds.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat
egg whites in bowl until it peaks.
Mix egg yolks and honey
and	fold
in
egg whites.
Add whipped cream when ready to serve.
Top with nutmeg.

title: gumdrop macaroons
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add chopped gumdrops.
Cream butter.
Add sugars gradually.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in gumdrop mixture.
Mix in nuts, oatmeal and coconut.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet (greased) and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove stems from mushrooms.
Dip caps in melted butter. Mix together 1/4 pound cream cheese, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Stuff the mushrooms.
Brown in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cake squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and butter by hand.
Pat mixture into 11 x 14-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs with blender.
Pour over cake mix.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Skin and seed the avocados.
Dice tomatoes.
In bowl, mash avocados with lemon juice.
Stir in tomato, salt, onion, garlic, chilies, and pinch of cilantro.
(To make it spicy, substitute jalapenos for the chilies.)

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
In a large bowl, beat 3 egg yolks with water until bowl is full.
Add sugar gradually while still beating until it mounds.
Add vanilla and flavoring.
Add baking powder and salt to flour, then add a little at a time, to egg mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: mrs. field's cookies(chocolate chip)
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake golf ball size cookies.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and jello.
Combine eggs, water, vegetable oil and strawberries.
Combine dry ingredients with wet. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple fruit salad
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and mandarin oranges into measuring cup.
If necessary, add water to make 1 2/3 cups.
Empty pudding mix powder into saucepan.
Stir in syrup.
Stirring frequently, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Mixture will bubble & become clear & thick.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in pineapple & mandarin oranges.
Let cool,
then refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: vegetable chicken pot pie
directions: In large skillet melt butter, add celery and stir over medium-high heat until crisp-tender.
Stir in soup, milk, onion powder, thyme and pepper; mix well.
Stir in vegetables and chicken/turkey, heat through.
Spoon in 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Arrange biscuits over hot filling.
bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: "beef stroganoff"
directions: Cut meat 1 inch long by 1/4 inch thick.
Coat with flour, garlic and pepper.
Brown in large skillet.
Remove meat.
Brown onions in same pan.
Slowly stir in water, soup and mushrooms. Cook until hot.
Add meat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix all together and drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet (I spray Pam on mine).
Bake at 450° for 10
minutes.
When done, brush tops with melted margarine (1/4 cup), 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt and parsley.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer the rice, onion, celery and soup mix, in that order.
Over this, pour the water.
Top with the browned sausage.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread the cream of mushroom soup on top.
Top with almonds and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: savory light pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl combine mustard, vinegar, oil, onions, garlic and tomato.
Let stand one hour at room temperature.
Cook pasta according to directions and add green pepper, broccoli and pea pods to pasta and water for the last minute of boiling.
Add drained pasta and vegetables to mixture.
Toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Garnish, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Beat well, preferably with an electric mixer until butter and sugar are light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In a separate bowl combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large measuring cup or glass, combine the milk and the vanilla.
Alternately add the flour mixture and the milk mixture to the butter mixture, mixing well after each addition, beginning and ending with the milk mixture.
It is very important that everything be very thoroughly combined.
Pour batter into a greased tube or Bundt cake pan.
To bake, bake 10 minutes at 275°, then without opening oven, increase temperature to 300° for 10 minutes, then finally increase temperature to 350° and continue baking for 60 more minutes.
Total baking time = 1 hour, 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then transfer to a plate. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chili rellenos
directions: In a medium-size bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, salt, milk and cheese.
Rinse chilies and remove seeds.
Place chilies in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over chilies and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Cook in boiling salted water about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Add eggs, milk, breadcrumbs, onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Blend well.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water until tender, drain and mash.
Add margarine, soup and most of the crumbs.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Dot with additional margarine.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: linguine with red clam sauce
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add pureed garlic and oregano. Saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes broken up with spoon and the liquid from the canned minced clams (reserve the clams), parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Toward the end of the hour, cook pasta.
Add the tablespoon salt to boiling water and gradually add pasta.
Cook, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally until tender.
Don't overcook.
Add canned minced clams to sauce and simmer for 5 minutes just to heat through.
Drain pasta and spoon in individual plates.
Spoon sauce over top and sprinkle with balance of chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cioppino
directions: Forty-five minutes before serving:
In hot oil, cook onion, pepper and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes plus liquid, wine, parsley, salt and basil; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: one pan chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan. Mix well with a fork.
Make 3 wells in mixture and add vanilla in 1st well, vinegar in 2nd well and oil in 3rd well.
Pour water over all and mix with a fork.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until center springs back.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add oats to boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add honey, margarine and salt.
When lukewarm, add yeast and stir in flour.
Add additional flour as you knead mixture until it is not sticky.
Place back in bowl. Cover and let rise until twice the size.
Knead again and form 2 loaves.
Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in 2 quarts water with a dash of salt and a teaspoon of oil.
Drain and mix with milk, sugar and egg.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and optional raisins.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm or cold.

title: nut rolls
directions: Scald milk and add oleo.
In large bowl, cool milk lightly; add yeast and mix well.
Add sugar, salt and eggs; beat well.
Add 4 cups flour at one time; beat with wooden spoon.
Add 4 more and beat.
Add last 2 cups and mix in bowl, then knead on a lightly floured board.
Return to bowl; cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: punch
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Double or triple this recipe for large crowds.

title: crisco cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and flour, then add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 Bundt cake pans.

title: pecan crunch fudge
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and evaporated milk in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat; stir in butterscotch morsels and marshmallow cream.
Beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth and just begins to cool.
Stir in chopped pecans, brickle chips and vanilla.
Spread mixture evenly into 2 buttered 8-inch square pans.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Mix and cook sugar, milk and salt until it boils.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth and spread in buttered pan.
Chill.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until no longer pink.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Alternate layers in order given and cook for 5 hours on low in 4-quart crock-pot.

title: hawaiian pineapple chicken
directions: Dip the pieces of chicken in milk; coat with flour.
Place in shallow baking pan; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Heat in saucepan the pineapple and cinnamon.
After chicken has baked for 1 hour, pour pineapple mixture over it and bake another 30 minutes.

title: mother's pickled beets
directions: Scrub beets good.
I used wire brush.
Cook beets until tender.
Reserve juice to use to pickle beets.
Boil beets 10 minutes in the sugar, vinegar and juice.
Hot pack and seal.

title: butterscotch morsels
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat.
Stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate over double boiler and let cool.
Beat 2 eggs and add to chocolate.
Separate 4 eggs.
Let whites stand at room temperature.
Beat egg whites until peaks form; add rest of yolks to chocolate mixture.
Add beaten egg whites to chocolate.
Beat heavy cream until whipped and fold everything together and refrigerate.
Pour into a mold pan.

title: piglet's pizza muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Split muffins in half, place split sides up in a shallow baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce onto the muffins, spreading it to the edges.
Top each muffin with a slice of cheese.
(Trim cheese slices so they are the same size as the muffins.)
Bake for 8-10 minutes or until cheese is browned slightly at the edges.

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter; press firmly into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: peach cheesecake lite
directions: In blender sprinkle unflavored gelatine over water.
Let stand 2 minutes.

title: no fail electric skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: Set your electric skillet at 280°.
Combine margarine, cream and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Unplug your skillet from heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat until ingredients are smooth and has lost it's shine.
Pour onto slightly buttered platter.
Let cool.

title: red valentine cake
directions: Combine food coloring and chocolate drink; let stand.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and cocoa paste.
Beat buttermilk; add to sugar mixture.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; beat well.
Mix in by hand the soda and vinegar.
Pour into two 8-inch greased baking pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: barrett's chicken, broccoli and penne
directions: Cook penne until al dente.
Keep warm while preparing chicken. Saute chicken in olive oil, lightly browning one side, then turn over.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, red pepper and broccoli.
Cook half a minute.
Add stock and butter.
Continue to saute until broccoli is cooked.
Toss in pasta and grated cheese.
Serve at once.
Serves 1.

title: dream squares
directions: Combine cake mix with 6 tablespoons oleo and 1 cup oatmeal. Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
Add 1 egg to remaining crumbs.
Mix well.
Press into pan.
Pour pie filling over crust. To reserved crumbs, add 1/4 cup oatmeal, 2 tablespoons oleo, nuts and brown sugar.
Mix.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 8.
Serve as bars or with whipped cream.

title: red lobster cheese rolls
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, water and cheese and drop by large spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix everything together well.
Drop 1 teaspoon of batter onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: small fruit cakes
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Put fruit, nuts, raisins and coconut in large bowl; dust with 1/2 cup of the flour.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder and salt; add alternately to butter-sugar-egg mix with pineapple juice. Begin and end with flour.
Add floured fruits, nuts and rum; stir only until well blended.
Grease and flour pans or use paper cups 2/3 full.
Top with half cherry and press down.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: overnite bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together egg whites, oil, sugar, yeast mixture, salt, water and flour until dough pulls away from side of bowl.
Cover; refrigerate dough at least 12 hours.
(Dough may be kept in refrigerator several days.)
On lightly floured surface, roll dough into balls, 2 inches in diameter.
Place balls 1/2 inch apart in 2 round greased cake pans, 8-inch each.
Let rise in warm place 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen (depending on size rolls).

title: hobo joe dinner
directions: Chop potatoes into very small pieces; saute in butter with diced onion, pepper and diced garlic clove.
When potatoes are almost cooked, add beef, crumbled.
Cook until beef is done; drain.
Serve with salad and a vegetable.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and bacon.
Mix well with cheese. Sprinkle with garlic powder. Combine mayonnaise with sour cream and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Keeps 2-3 days in refrigerator.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk together. Beat for 1 minute. Add whipped topping, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° until light brown.

title: edith's hungarian goulash
directions: Place meat in pot (slow cooker).
Cover with sliced onion. Combine garlic, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika and mustard.
Stir in water and pour over meat.
Cook in slow cooker 9 to 10 hours.

title: creamed ham and hominy
directions: Place hominy in strainer.
Wash under cold water; drain.
Pour cream into saucepan.
Stir in flour until completely blended. Bring to a boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add ham and hominy.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf - united methodist women
directions: Soak bread in the milk (leave set aside).
Mix hamburger with onions, spices and beaten egg.
Then add soaked bread.
Shape into loaf.
Cover with ketchup.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: whipped sweet dish
directions: Thaw whipped topping for an hour.
In a medium-sized bowl, combine whipped topping with condensed milk.
Now mix in all of the drained fruits.
Fold in walnuts.

title: taco bean salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
This is quick and crunchy. Top with sour cream or salsa.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve over potatoes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Reserve dry soup for topping.
Stir together soups, water, milk and rice.
Place the chicken in the soup mixture and sprinkle the dry onion soup over the top.
No salt or other seasonings are needed.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours in covered roaster or large casserole dish.

title: baby plum bread
directions: Mix sugar, spices and self-rising flour.
Add oil and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each is added.
Fold in vanilla, baby plums and chopped nuts.
Turn into 2 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mote tortilla soup
directions: Brown chicken with onion.
Drain, add rest of ingredients into crock pot or stew pot.
simmer for 6 hr.
Top with Tostitos and cheese when serving.

title: lebanese rolled cabbage
directions: This same stuffing can be used for rolled grape leaves or stuffed yellow-necked squash.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine yams, oleo, sugar, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle small amount of sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: bacon-wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Drain the water chestnuts.
Pour the soy sauce over them. Place them in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Heat the oven to broil.
Drain the water chestnuts.
Wrap a half slice of bacon around each chestnut.
Hold the bacon in place by pushing a toothpick through the bacon and into the chestnut.
Place the chestnuts on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Broil them until the bacon is brown.

title: elgin's enchiladas
directions: Place taquitos, in a casserole dish, in a single layer.
Cover with chili and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: lemoned carrots
directions: Boil carrots in small amount of water until tender.
Combine carrots, lemonade concentrate and cloves in small saucepan. Simmer 5 minutes.
Let cool; chill thoroughly.
Drain carrots; remove cloves.
Serve on lettuce.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine cake mix, yeast and salt.
Add water and flour to make a soft dough (dough will be quite sticky).
Cover; let rise until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir down dough and spoon irregular balls of dough into bowl of flour to lightly cover.
Spoon into lightly greased muffin tins.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup and water and bring to a boil.
Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces and drop in hot soup and cook until biscuits are done.
Add margarine; salt and pepper to taste if desired.
Quick meal!

title: salmon cakes
directions: Place salmon in mixing bowl, stir in the mushrooms, celery, onion, chives, garlic, egg white and basil.
Shape into 2 patties. Heat vegetable oil in a saute pan until hot.
Add salmon cakes, cook for 2 minutes on each side.
Careful when turning them over. Serve with steamed vegetables.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into freezer can.
Freeze according to the directions of your ice cream freezer.

title: deep dish pizza casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Add peppers, mix lightly.
Brown beef, drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and onions. Spoon dinner into 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Top with beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter, and milk until soft ball forms in cold water.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, add other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes in a slow oven of 350°. Cool and serve.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter and oil until golden and limp.
Stir in flour.
Add liquid and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, sugars and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly before removing to paper covered counter to cool.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: cheesy layered salad
directions: Layer half of lettuce in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Line sides of bowl with egg slices.
Spoon peas evenly over lettuce.
Sprinkle with remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top. Cover salad tightly and chill 24 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger dinner
directions: Brown chuck in oil; drain off fat.
Combine ground chuck with rest of ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are done.

title: asparagus lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, cook asparagus in a small amount of water until crisp-tender, about 7 minutes; drain and set aside.
In another large saucepan, melt butter.
Cook garlic and onion on low heat until transparent.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in cream cheese, lemon juice, peel, hot pepper sauce and nutmeg.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Spread about 3/4 cup sauce in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer with 3 noodles, a fourth of the sauce and a third of the asparagus and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers twice.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce (dish will be full).
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: fideos con chorizo
directions: Brown chorizo in skillet on medium heat and drain.
Puree in blender tomatoes, onions and garlic.
Transfer to large deep skillet or saucepan.
Bring to boil; stir consistently for 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth and vermicelli noodles.
Continue to boil and stir for 10 minutes.
Add chorizo.
Simmer until all liquids are absorbed.
Slice avocado over noodles and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: smoked fish spread  #1
directions: Skin the smoked fish and remove it from the bones. Break fish into small pieces and put it in a large bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Serve on crackers or bread. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix sour cream with milk.
Add 1 can peppers (undrained), Velveeta cheese and rice.
Spoon in large casserole dish.
Garnish with 1 can peppers (drained), sharp cheese and paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hastarta(quick torte)
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar; add extract.
Sift in flour and salt; lastly add the melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a nonstick or greased and floured cake pan (one layer cake pan will do).
Sprinkle the nuts or coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in the pan.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper. Dip breasts in melted butter, then in crumbs, coating heavily. Pour any left over crumb mixture over chicken. Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: apricot bars
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and pinch of salt.
Mix with sugar and oatmeal.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pat 2/3 of the mixture into pan firmly. Spread with jam, then cover with the rest of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vampire punch
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar and water to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple, strawberries and juices.
Chill.
Add cooled sugar syrup to fruit mixture.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add club soda and ice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine and cream sugar, margarine and eggs; add pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts. Butter 4 (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Fill pans half full with batter.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight before using.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all together; pour in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice on bottom of baking dish.
Mix the cream soups (any kind) with 1 can water; pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice and soup.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil; bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: apple cinnamon jelly
directions: Combine juice and pectin in large pan.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Add sugar and candy.
Bring to a boil again.
Stir constantly.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Skim and pour in jars and seal.
Makes 6 1/2 (1/2 pints).

title: noodle kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except noodles and almonds.
Add noodles to mixture; toss to coat.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spoon noodle mixture into pan; sprinkle evenly with almonds.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: chile beans
directions: Cook beans until barely tender.
Add onion, chile, salt, spices and tomatoes. Continue cooking until tender.
Remove from heat and add oil and cheese.
Beat until beans are well mashed. Makes 5 cups.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with wax paper.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and spices together and pour into lined pan.
Pour dry cake mix over mixture evenly and pat nuts on cake mix.
Spoon melted butter over cake mix and nuts evenly.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until light golden brown. Cool for several hours, then loosen edges with knife and invert on a tray.
Peel off waxed paper.
Top with Cool Whip.
Enjoy!

title: hawaiian dream pie
directions: Drain juice from pineapple thoroughly.
Blend into Cool Whip and lemon juice; add milk.
Pour into shells and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill around 3 hours.
This recipe is for two pies.
For one pie, use half.

title: pastry cheese ball
directions: Thaw patty shells and roll into an 8-inch circle.
Remove wax coating on cheese.
Cover cheese with pastry and seal edges well. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes, then boil in salted water until soft.
Allow to cool, then mash.
Add the remaining ingredients to the mashed potatoes.
Mix together well and form into oblong croquettes.
Fry until golden brown in hot olive oil.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together first six ingredients; then add the dry ingredients.
Refrigerate and chill for one to two hours; afterwards, form into balls and roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet, and press with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
This recipe makes a flat cookie.
I like a browned cookie, so you be the judge on your time.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cashew  chicken
directions: Determine the amount of rice that you will need and make according to the
directions.
In a large bowl, combine the first six ingredients together (chicken, oil, garlic, vinegar, red pepper flakes and black pepper), and set it aside.
Then heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large nonstick skillet over high heat until it smokes.
Add carrot and stir-fry for 2-3 minutes.
Add in the chicken mixture to the skillet and cook for another 3-4 minutes. Toss in the red bell pepper and the chestnuts.
Heat through for 1-2 minutes.
Add the hoisin sauce to coat evenly.
Place cooked rice on serving platter, pour chicken over rice, and garnish with cashews and onions.
Serves 4.

title: veeta's homemade pineapple cake
directions: Cream sugar and Parkay together.
Add eggs, flour and milk. Mix well.
Stir in oil and flavoring.
Hand beat 350 strokes or 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour in four greased pans and cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Prepare broccoli; mix all ingredients.
Toss the still warm broccoli with the dressing until well mixed and chill.
Serves 6.

title: quick noodle casserole
directions: Prepare oven to 325°.
Bring broth and water to boil in saucepan.
Add noodles and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in cheese and mushrooms.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is hot.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk until blended; add drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Blend together well.
Fold in nuts.
Divide mixture and place 1/2 into each pie crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: sunflower salad with ramen noodles
directions: Crush noodles and drop into a bowl. Add cole slaw mix, sunflower seeds and almonds; mix. In small bowl, mix 2 packages flavoring from Ramen noodles, oil, sugar and vinegar. Mix until all is dissolved. Pour over noodle mixture. Let stand in the refrigerator before serving. Keeps 2 days.

title: dad's salad dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a blender.
Refrigerate until cold. Serve on green salad.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together (low heat).
Cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix together with hands, let cool. Sprinkle coconut on wax paper and spoon mixture over coconut. Sprinkle more coconut on top and make a log roll.
Roll up in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix the sweetened condensed milk, pineapple and lemon juice together well.
Add nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into baked graham cracker crusts.
Chill 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Makes two 9-inch or three 8-inch pies.

title: untossed salad
directions: In layers in large glass bowl:
lettuce and spinach (small pieces), peas, crumbled eggs, crumbled bacon, green scallions (cut finely), mayonnaise and grated Swiss cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rich pastry
directions: *Add flour until it is a stiff pastry.
You may need up to 3 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage partly done.
Layer bread, cheese and sausage. Beat eggs in milk, add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour egg mixture over top, press down to be sure all bread is soaked.

title: tomato lime pickles
directions: Soak clean
green tomatoes in water and lime mixture in crockery or
enamelware
for
hours
or overnight.
Wash 3 times in clean
water and soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours. Combine remaining
ingredients
and bring to a low boil.
Stir until sugar is
dissolved.
Add green tomatoes and soak 5 to 6 hours or
overnight.
Boil
pickles
in
soaking liquid for 35 minutes.
Fill
sterilized
quart
jars
with
green tomatoes. Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and slice. In covered baking dish, layer potatoes, onions and Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Spread beans in bottom of a glass baking dish; put beef evenly over that layer.
Shake taco seasoning over beef, then pour jar of sauce on.
In a separate bowl, beat softened cream cheese and sour cream for 2 minutes. Spread this on top and cover with shredded cheese.
Dice pepper and onion for your next layer; spread evenly on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Remove and top with diced tomato.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serve hot with chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Combine all dry ingredients and add; do not overmix.
Add nuts and vanilla and pour in 2 large or 3 medium loaf pans.
(Makes 6 mini loaves). Bake at 350° from 35 to 45 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: cheese and spaghetti
directions: Boil the spaghetti straws until just tender; set aside.
Have the grated cheese ready.
Melt margarine; set aside to cool, then beat in eggs, one at a time, real well.
Add milk.
Drain spaghetti straws and layer 1/2 of the straws, 1/2 the margarine, egg and milk mixture and 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Repeat.
Cook in moderately hot oven (350°) until it is bubbly hot.
This makes a delicious side dish.

title: shrimp-vegetable casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package; drain.
Drain asparagus and peas.
Put shrimp, noodles, asparagus, peas and croutons together in large pan.
Stir mushroom soup and milk together.
Pour over shrimp and vegetable mixture in pan.
Add seasoning.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in flour, salt, baking powder, buttermilk, coconut extract and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients with oatmeal and hot water.
Add chips and nuts.
Mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan.
Add green pepper and onion; saute until slightly tender.
Mix pork and beans, brown sugar and ketchup together in a bowl.
Add green pepper, onion and bacon which has been broken into pieces.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until slightly crusted.

title: australian goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions and set aside.
Saute garlic and onion until clear.
Add hamburger and cook until crumbly.
Add everything else, except cheese. Simmer on top of the stove until well blended.
Add Cheddar cheese last.

title: sugar and nuts
directions: Grind together equal amounts of Longhorn (Colby) cheese and salted cocktail peanuts.
Add relish and desired spice blend or Miracle Whip to desired taste and spreading consistency.
Good on crackers, fancy bread or sandwich with lettuce.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Arrange in a casserole.
Arrange chunks of boned chicken on top of broccoli. Make sauce of soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over the chicken.
Cover with bread crumbs, cheese and dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with a green salad.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Mix flour, milk, sugar and baking powder in a bowl and pour over melted butter.
Spoon peaches on top (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Pour over bread crumbs and cornbread.
Add beaten eggs and broth. (If too stiff, add a little water.)
Pour into greased baking pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook and devein shrimp.
Cook macaroni until done.
Rinse starch off.
Chop onions, green peppers and shrimp.
Mix with macaroni.
Add Old Bay seasoning and the rest of ingredients. Stir well.
Add more Old Bay seasoning and Tabasco if needed.
Add enough mayonnaise and salad dressing to make it loose.

title: party pecan balls
directions: Cream 1/2 cup powdered sugar and butter until smooth.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease 2 baking sheets. Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on prepared baking sheets. Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in an airtight container.

title: spiced potatoes
directions: Mix
vegetable oil and melted butter in casserole dish. Cut up potatoes with peeling on.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over potatoes. Sprinkle
remaining seasonings over potatoes.
Toss and bake at 450° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Spray Pam onto 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread and 1 pad butter slice; mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle half onto first layer of bread.
Repeat bread, butter and sugar mixture.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla together and pour over bread.
Refrigerate 12 hours and bake at 350°, uncovered.

title: pork and apple casserole
directions: Place apples in well-greased baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine well with apples.
Coat pork chops with bread crumbs.
Arrange pork chops over apples.
Bake, covered, for 1/2 hour at 375°, then uncover for about 20 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a casserole dish, slightly beat eggs, then add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Add beer to biscuit mix.
Stir well.
Turn out on a floured board, roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
These smell like yeast when baking.
Alcohol is baked out.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter until smooth.
Add 2 eggs at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Add sugar gradually; blend thoroughly.
Fill sugar box 3/4 full with all-purpose flour.
Add gradually and cream to butter mixture.
Add vanilla; blend and add pecans and fold into mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Could take 1 1/4 hours according to oven.
Top will crack as most pound cakes do.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: No need for a pie crust and no need to peel apples.
Core and slice apples.
Fill 9 or 10-inch pie plate 2/3 full with apples. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: orange pecan bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine eggs, melted butter, orange juice, orange peel and water. Add all at once to flour mixture. Stir quickly until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in pecans. Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack. Slice and serve with butter.

title: ensalada nopales("cactus salad")
directions: Drain and rinse cactus in cold water.
Put in a medium size bowl with onion, tomatoes, avocado and dressing; chill.
Just before serving stir in pork rinds.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Beat eggs until frothy. Add sugar and beat until mixture is pale yellow. Add melted butter, melted white chocolate, vanilla, salt and flour. Stir in chocolate chips and white chocolate chips. Bake at 350° in greased 8 in. square pan about 30 minutes. Cool completely before cutting.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, cool, peel and grate.
Mix together rest of ingredients and fold into the grated potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, then uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine ground turkey or chuck with soup and enchilada sauce. Pour into cake pan.
Top with Doritos.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Place cheese on top and place back in the oven just long enough to melt cheese.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with chopped ripe olives.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and stir in the Parmesan cheese.
Put into a buttered baking dish.
Place chicken on top of noodles.
Add salt and pepper if needed.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: sauce for baked fish
directions: Chop onions and bell pepper; saute in butter until tender. Add lemon juice, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add to vegetable mixture along with the red wine. Stir until mixture thickens.
Spoon over baked or broiled fish.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt butter; add apple pie filling and sugar.
Continue beating, stirring occasionally, until sugar melts.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients; mix raisins, pecans and candied fruit with dry ingredients.
Pour into foil lined 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: porky pine meatballs
directions: Take tomato soup and 1 cup of rice and put in large pan on medium heat.
Take hamburger, onion, chili powder, garlic, pepper, salt, egg and other cup of rice and mix.
Form into meatballs. Brown in skillet.
Put meatballs in large pan with soup and rice. Cook on medium heat for 2 hours.

title: green rice
directions: Simmer the broccoli in water until tender. Drain the rice before adding the broccoli. Bake for 2 to 2.5 hours.

title: ham and pea salad
directions: In a serving bowl, combine the peas, ham, cheese, and onions. Pour dressing over the top, toss to coat evenly.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil. Add orange jello and dissolve. Cool. Stir in cool whip and buttermilk. Add nuts if desired. Let congeal.

title: jiffy hollandaise sauce
directions: Melt margarine; set aside and keep warm.
In blender container, combine egg substitute, lemon juice, dry mustard and pepper.
Blend on medium speed for 1 minute.
Continue blending; remove lid and slowly add melted margarine in thin stream.
After margarine is added, blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Sauce will be thick and creamy.
Serve with hot vegetables or fish. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Process on high for 1 minute or until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Best if made day ahead. If you are going to use to whole recipe, will store for a long time, but you may need to run it through the blender again before use.
Makes 2 cups.
I usually use this on spinach salad made with bean sprouts and crumbled bacon.

title: ground cherry marmalade
directions: Wash cherries and steam until soft.
Cook lemon and orange together about 5 minutes.
Put together (cherries and orange, lemon mixture) in kettle and add sugar.
Boil until thick, about 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Beat pudding and milk together until smooth and fold in Cool Whip. Spread half of mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over pudding.
Top with remaining pudding.
Cover with third layer of crackers. Melt chocolate and butter.
Beat remaining ingredients into chocolate until smooth.
Spread over top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: cherry yum-yum pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press in bottom of a large, oblong pan, leaving enough crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Whip the Dream Whip with milk; combine Dream Whip and cheese mixture.
Add layer of this to graham cracker crust, then layer of pie filling, then repeat.
Sprinkle on top some graham cracker crumbs.
Place in refrigerator overnight until cold.

title: hungarian flourless cake
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Beat egg yolks with sugar until smooth.
Mix baking powder, nuts, butter and chocolate with egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly fold in mixture. Bake in layer cake pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Watch carefully.

title: marshmallow treats deluxe
directions: Melt the margarine over low heat. Stir in the marshmallows until all are melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in the butterscotch morsels until well blended. Add the Rice Krispies and mix well (it will be sticky).
Press lightly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and cut when cool.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; stir often.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water in mixer bowl.
Beat in sour cream until smooth.
Add cranberry sauce, beating until blended. Stir in nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: magic peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place small balls of dough on ungreased baking sheet.
Using a fork dipped in flour, flatten balls of dough in a crisscross design.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in blender.
Cream butter and cream cheese; add sugar.
Beat pudding and milk and add Cool Whip to mixture.
Blend cream cheese mixture with the pudding mixture.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Press in the bottom of your pan.
Melt 2 cups of chocolate chips.
Pour over mixture in pan. When slightly hard, cut into squares.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions; drain well.
In a saucepan, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.

title: heath bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light. Add beaten egg yolk, vanilla and sifted flour.
Spread thinly on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add raisins and bread.
Mix well. Put in greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: salad bowl puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Heat water and butter to boiling.
Add Bisquick all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about 1 1/2 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Continue beating until smooth.
Spread in pie pan (do not spread up sides). Bake until puffed and dry in center, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Just before serving, fill with salad.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6 to 8. Can be frozen up to 1 week.

title: cold eggplant appetizer(microwave)
directions: Rinse eggplant and place on microwaveproof roasting rack. Pierce skin in several places.
Cook on High for 6 to 7 minutes, or until soft.
Set aside to cool.

title: minestrone
directions: Heat oil in large heavy-based saucepan; add bones and cook, stirring, until well browned all over.
Add water; bring to boil. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove and discard bones from broth. Bring broth to boil; stir in tomatoes and macaroni.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in carrots, leek, zucchini, beans, paste and sugar.
Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes or until leek is tender.
Stir in spinach and parsley just before serving.

title: vegetable-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 1-quart baking dish.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and blend well.
Turn into dish. Bake until heated through, about 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Cut up water chestnuts and onion.
Drain beans.
Mix everything together. Season to taste.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rocky tops
directions: In medium bowl, cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth. Shape rounded teaspoons of dough into balls.
Pinch or shape each ball to a rounded point, to resemble a chocolate candy kiss.
The cookie top will flatten slightly during baking, only small lump remains.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Mix next 3 ingredients.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Cut into squares.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
With an electric mixer, cream the cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme.
Add lemon juice.
Mix well.
Serve with assorted fruit slices.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream
together first 4 ingredients. Combine the next 3 ingredients
and add to creamed mixture alternately with 1 cup of buttermilk.
In a separate small bowl mix together vinegar and soda,
then
add
to
creamed mixture.
Add food coloring last. Bake as a regular cake approximately 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions and set aside.
In another bowl, cream softened cream cheese with electric mixer.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Fold Dream Whip into mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker shell.
Spoon pie filling on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and mix in sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and bananas.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased 1-pound loaf bread pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble. Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Blend in soup, water, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Add potatoes, parsley and bacon. Heat; stir occasionally.

title: eggs in a paper bag
directions: You will need 12 paper bags (1/2 to 1 pound size), 12 toasting sticks and 4 yards of string.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions.
Chop all vegetables.
Add spices, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cook on low heat until mixture thickens. Must be stirred frequently to prevent sticking.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk, sugar and seasonings.
Blend well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin batter.
Sprinkle walnuts over cake mix.
Drizzle butter or margarine over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.
Good substitute for pumpkin pie for a crowd.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese and catsup.
Pour into greased casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; dot with catsup.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Peel and cut up zucchini and chop onion.
Add a little water; cook in a covered pan until done, then drain. In bowl, add Stove Top dressing, melted margarine, zucchini, onion, cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix altogether.
Put in a baking dish and cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Grease and flour a 17 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake mix using pineapple juice instead of water.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, milk and pudding together.
Spread on cool cake.
Top with drained pineapple and then the Cool Whip.

title: cheese soup
directions: Fry green pepper, garlic and onion in butter.
Stir in flour. Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 1 cup beef stock and milk.
Bring to a simmer and add the rest of the ingredients. Stir until cheese melts.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Let stand overnight. Keeps well.

title: glazed cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except glaze until dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes.
Turn on cloth covered board well dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll to coat; shape into ball. Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.
Bake on greased cookie sheet until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread with Vanilla Glaze while warm. Makes 10 biscuits.

title: easy sodas
directions: Dissolve soft drink mix and sugar in water in nonmetal bowl or pitcher.
Stir in soda.
Place a small scoop of ice cream in each of 6 tall glasses.
Stir in soda mixture; top with a second scoop of ice cream.
Makes about 2-quarts or 6 large servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Heat over low until well blended. This is a good sauce for bar-b-q chicken or pork or beef sandwiches.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onions and carrots in margarine.
Add chicken broth and simmer 20 minutes.
Then add potato soup and milk and heat until hot.
Add cheese and sour cream.

title: dressing for cabbage slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
This is enough for a 3 pound cabbage.

title: regal chocolate sauce
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and water.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°). Remove from heat and add chocolate. Stir until chocolate melts.
Add vanilla. Slowly add evaporated milk and mix thoroughly. Cool. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: savory chicken stew
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook half of the chicken until browned, stirring often. Remove; set aside. Repeat with remaining chicken. Pour off fat. In same skillet, combine soup, milk, potatoes, carrots, broccoli and pepper. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover; cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Return chicken to skillet. Cover; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally, if desired. Sprinkle with cracked black pepper. Serves 4.

title: bacon buttermilk topper for baked potato
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon over hot baked potato.
Can store in refrigerator up to 5 days, covered.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper. Spread beef in pie plate, sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and biscuit mix until well mixed.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until well browned and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes before cutting.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Combine salmon with cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, eggs and bread crumbs and make small balls.
Drop into a boiling mixture of ginger ale and catsup.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Add pineapple and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together and add to pineapple mixture. Stir in pecans. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: yummy fruit dip
directions: Combine milk and pudding, mixing well.
Stir in sour cream. Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add spices.
Add tomato products. Bring to a boil, then simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add sugar.
Mix together beaten egg, milk and oatmeal.
Then add to dry ingredients and stir until blended. Stir in melted butter. Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove at once from tins.
This makes 12 average size muffins.

title: mother's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: p. p. pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie crust.
Chill.

title: bonbons
directions: Let the butter, milk and confectioners sugar come to a bubble. Add either coconut, chocolate, peanut butter, raisins, dates or nuts.
Shape and frost with melted chocolate chips.

title: low-fat freezer ice cream
directions: Pour 1 cup of milk in saucepan; put vanilla in and cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Remove.
Pour milk mix in a bowl and chill.
Combine evaporated milk, sugar, egg substitute and remaining cup of 2% milk in mixture. Stir with wire whisk until blended.
Pour into freezer for 1 hour (1/2 gallon freezer).

title: white salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix juice and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip, along with pineapple, and add marshmallows (I quarter the marshmallows with my kitchen scissors).
Next, stir all together real good and chill overnight.

title: bernee's shepherd's pie
directions: Put cooked hamburger in rectangular dish.
Top with slices of tomato.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Layer grated cheese on top and heat in oven until warmed through at 350° for about 25 minutes. You may have to cover with foil to keep from getting too brown.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix corn meal with the salmon; add corn meal to absorb liquid and form into soft patties.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Patties may be fried or baked.

title: blueberry jello(great for july 4th)
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve black raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add blueberries and juice.
Gel.

title: zucchini torte
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix very well.
Do not use mixer.
Lightly oil 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until cooked through.
Cut in squares.
Serve warm or cold.

title: roast turkey
directions: Remove giblets and neck.
Wash turkey with cold water; clean out cavity.
Sprinkle entire turkey with seasoned salt, including cavity.
Poke 6 to 8 holes into turkey breast.
Insert bell pepper, onion and bacon pieces into holes.
Layer entire breast of turkey with bacon slices.
Rub Kitchen Bouquet over turkey. Stuff cavity with dressing, if desired.
Pat a little oil over skin of turkey and spread 1 tablespoon of oil into bottom of pan. Place turkey in pan and cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 4 hours.
Uncover and let turkey brown completely, about 45 minutes more.

title: oven meal
directions: Use ingredients to your family's needs.
Saute hamburger, onions and peppers in oil.
Layer all ingredients, then repeat layers.
Put bacon on top.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender before adding flour which has been beaten with enough water to make a thin paste.
Then cook until thick and seal in jars.

title: bust-your-girdle pie
directions: Break cookies, covering bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften ice cream and spread over cookie layer.
Warm fudge sauce slightly and drizzle over ice cream layer.
Freeze.
Spread Cool Whip over fudge layer.
Cover with foil; freeze until serving.

title: mary's stuffed peppers
directions: In a large frying pan on low heat, dice garlic and brown in the olive oil.
Pour in 1/2 can of tomatoes and simmer.
In a large bowl, mix hamburg, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and bread; then tomato mixture.
Wash peppers; cut in half and remove seeds. Stuff peppers.
Place peppers on lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Spoon remaining tomatoes over top of peppers and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Add milk and mashed bananas. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased cake pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon coconut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
With sharp knife, peel lemons, removing a thin yellow layer only (no white part).
In food processor, put lemon peels and sugar, pulsing 4 to 5 times, then let machine run for 1 minute until peel and sugar are minced.
Add butter, sugar and lemon juice and process 20 seconds or until well blended.
Add shredded coconut and flour and pulse 4 to 6 times until well blended.
Form dough into walnut size balls and place 2 inches apart on a lightly buttered baking sheet.
Bake in oven for 15 to 17 minutes on lower third shelf of oven until edges just start to brown.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: best-ever orange sponge cake
directions: Place egg whites in large glass mixing bowl; let warm about 1 hour.
Sift flour with salt; set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar; continue to beat until stiff peaks form.
In small mixing bowl, beat the egg yolks on high until very thick and lemon colored, about 3 minutes.
Gradually add remaining sugar; beat until smooth.
At low speed, blend flour mixture and orange juice alternately into egg yolk mixture.
Add orange peel; with whisk or rubber spatula, add this to egg white mixture.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar as soon as cool enough to remove from pan.

title: best ever minute fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk, bring to a boil.
Boil one minute. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add butter, peanut butter, vanilla, cocoa powder and nuts.

title: paul's guacamole salad
directions: Peel, remove seed, and mash avocados.
Mash everything together.
Chill for at least one hour to re-hydate the guacamole mix ingredients.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Prepare or secure pie shells.
Make crumbs of brown sugar, flour and butter or margarine, then set aside.
Pour boiling water over molasses and baking soda.
Pour this into the unbaked pie shells and then put the crumbs in carefully.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 large (9-inch) and 1 small pies.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add melted butter, egg and vanilla.
Stir in candy pieces.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: egg and sausage scramble
directions: Cook and stir sausage and heat until light brown; drain off grease and put sausage in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat eggs, milk and salt and stir in cheese.
Pour over sausage and sprinkle with croutons.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: rhubarb jam(with either blueberry or strawberry)
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar and let stand overnight in Tupperware bowl, then add blueberry or strawberry pie filling and pour into a stainless steel kettle.
Boil 15 minutes.
Stir constantly and then remove from heat and add jello.
Stir.
Put into freezer type containers.
Very good.
Freezes well.

title: wedding punch(serving size: 50)
directions: Soften sherbet in fruit juices and water.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over large block of ice or ice ring in punch bowl.
Punch will bubble effectively during early part of serving. Dry ice substituted for ice block will give smoking effect. Brighter green color can be achieved with food coloring.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain any grease.
Add green beans, tomato juice and chili powder.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Add 4 1/2 cups water.
Bring to boil, stirring well.
Add rice.
Remove from heat and cover. Allow to cook; fluff.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well for several days.

title: pink cloud
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with cherry juice.
Cut cherries. Drain pineapple and add 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip (defrosted).
Fold in marshmallows.

title: sweet potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sweet potatoes, water, parsnip, onion, bouillon granules and nutmeg.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are very tender.
Transfer to a blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Return mixture to saucepan.
Stir in milk and heat through.

title: mahogany chicken
directions: Lightly sprinkle both sides of chicken with garlic powder; let stand 15 minutes.
Lightly coat chicken with flour.
Brown in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Turn chicken over. Sprinkle onion evenly over chicken.
Cook until chicken is golden brown.

title: sourdough bread
directions: First Day (a.m.):
Make feed starter with first 4 ingredients. Mix and let set at room temperature all day in a covered container.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Bone and chop into chunks.
Keep broth until just warm.
Dip tortillas into it.
Line 9 x 13-inch dish with tortillas.
Spread chicken over tortillas, then onion, pepper and undiluted soup.
Cover well with a layer of grated cheese.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes (mashed or blended) over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon fillet in parchment
directions: Fold a 16 x 12-inch (or larger) piece of parchment paper in half and crease.
Unfold paper and place the salmon fillet in one half.
Sprinkle fish with fresh dill sprigs and julienned leek and carrot.
Fold paper over and crimp edges.
Place on a plate and microwave on High for 4 1/2 minutes or just until opaque.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serves 4.

title: angel torte
directions: In bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water. Add strawberries that have been thawed. Chill until starts to thicken.

title: honey golden chicken
directions: Rub chicken with lemon. Sprinkle with 1 tsp. ginger and salt. Combine oil, honey and remaining ginger, and brush chicken with this mixture. Roast in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 - 2 hours, basting occasionally with with honey mixture.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into baking dish; top with the 1/2 cup of Ritz crackers and pecans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: maple walnut fudge
directions: Drop in heaping cup of Love.

title: wintertime potato soup
directions: Melt butter in large soup pot.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook potatoes and cabbage in chicken stock in separate pan.
Then add soup to soup pot.
Add spice and light cream; return to simmer.
Do not boil after adding cream.
Serves 6. Delicious with dark rye or wheat bread.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip, then the pineapple and strawberries.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Place in loaf pan, either an 8 1/2 or 9-inch.
Freeze overnight.
After slicing, let thaw slightly before serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain completely.
Add onions and green pepper.
Stir and cook until onions are clear.
Stir in spices. Add whole, peeled tomatoes (do not drain) and cut them up with spoon while stirring.
Add tomato sauce and red beans.
Allow to simmer for 5 more minutes.
Add cayenne pepper to taste.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour melted butter on top.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: lasagne(large group)
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain and rinse. Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.

title: tupperware bowl double crust for pie or pasties
directions: Use large Tupperware bowl with lid.
Put all the ingredients together in bowl.
Seal, burp and shake.
Remove seal and add 1/4 cup ice water.
Reseal and shake until forms a ball.
May have to work together slightly.
Use like regular pie crust or roll out in circle for pasties.
Handle very little for very flaky crust.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter with cream cheese until soft.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar creaming until light and fluffy.
Blend in 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and celery in butter.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together and cook until cheese is melted.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Cook rice for 25 minutes. Drain. While hot, put in bowl and add 1 package raspberry jello and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir well. Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Refrigerate overnight.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream shortening, adding sugar and eggs gradually until smooth.
Stir in mincemeat and add flour gradually.
Drop on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: copper penny carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Cool.
Add green pepper, celery and onion.
In small bowl, add tomato soup, oil, sugar, salt and mustard.
Stir well.
Pour over carrot mixture and mix well.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate.
Let set several hours or overnight, to flavor well.
Keeps for days.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening and eggs.
Add extract.
Mix until it makes a dough.
Divide dough, 2/3 for a base.
Pat the 2/3 of the dough in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Spread 1 cup of the preserves on top.
Crumble the remaining dough on top of the preserves.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven or until browned on top.

title: bank punch
directions: Mix Kool Aid and sugar until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice.
Add enough water to gallon jug to make 1 gallon.

title: aunt "mil's" sand dabs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Work rest in with hands.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on while hot.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onions till slightly soft.
Move onions to side and cook garlic for one minute.
Mix into onions. Add remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Stir to mix.
Cover and simmer gently, 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and heat just enough to warm them through.
Do not allow them to cook.
May be served cold.

title: quick strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is coarse.
Add milk, vanilla and beaten egg. Mix with spoon until fairly smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450° until light brown.
Serve with sweetened crushed strawberries. Makes 4 generous servings.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix everything together and shape into ball.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, liquid smoke, salt and salmon; mix thoroughly.
Chill for several hours.
Combine nuts and parsley.
Shape salmon mixture into a log 14-inches long and 2-inches in diameter.
Roll in nut mixture.
Makes 1 log.

title: apple crisp(a microwave dessert)
directions: Place apples in 8 x 8 x 2-inch microsafe dish.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon flour in bowl.
Toss with apples to coat.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cook on Full power for 11 to 13 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: steve's chili
directions: Brown meat thoroughly and drain off all possible grease.
Add everything else and simmer hard with lid on loosely for 1 1/2 hours, then take lid off and simmer until thick enough to suit you.
You can add more hot spices, such as cayenne, if you like. Recipe is easily halved.
Better, day old.
Great frozen and reheated.

title: pork and rice
directions: Cover pork with water; add onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until pork is tender.
Add mushroom soup, rice, salt and pepper.
Cook slow until rice is done.
Cooks better with cover on.

title: spicy cabbage
directions: Shred the first 4 ingredients together.
Put sugar on mixture and set aside.
Bring to boil remaining ingredients.
Pour over shredded cabbage mixture and let stand overnight.

title: nina's spinach
directions: Wash and pat spinach leaves dry.
Tear into bite size pieces. In large saucepan, simmer spinach with a small amount of water for 3 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat oil, soy sauce and sugar in a skillet.
Add spinach and onion.
Cook and toss until spinach is well coated, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in water chestnuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese delight
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spitini
directions: You will need 6 to 8 meat skewers.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend cornstarch, 1 1/2 cups sugar and salt in saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir half of mixture slowly into egg yolks.
Return to pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and juice.

title: apple pie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter as for pie crust.
Mix in egg yolks (mixture will be crumbly). Press half of the mixture in bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
May also use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set remaining half of mixture aside.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a small pan, mash 1 cup green and overripe berries.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix cornstarch in water until dissolved.
Pour in pan with berries.
Cook over medium heat until mixture turns almost transparent.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Add lemon juice.
Set off burner to cool.

title: green beans
directions: If necessary, add small amount of water.
Melt shortening in saucepan.
Simmer onions one minute in shortening.
Add green beans, salt and sugar.
Cook until done.
Stir often and cook slow.

title: lil's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, flavorings and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beat until well mixed and fluffy. Add one cup flour and 1/3 cup milk; mix with spatula and continue to beat until well mixed. Add baking powder to remaining flour and add with remaining milk to batter. Pour into greased and floured steeple pan. Bake in a 315° oven for one hour and 25 minutes. Do not open door. Be sure cake is golden brown and is pulling away from pan before removing from oven. Frost if desired.

title: cold tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Run over with cold water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Dice up egg; add to macaroni in a bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix.
Serve alone or on salad.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in paper sack.
Bring oleo, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Then add soda and stir.
Pour mixture over popcorn in sack and shake.
Put in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes, remove and shake.
Repeat 3 times total, pour on counter to cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
all
except flour.
(Make oat or millet flour by blending
grain
in
blender.)
Add
flour to creamed mixture. Form into balls.
Flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs one at a time and stir well.
Combine flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out in triangles. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool, then put them in 1 cup of sugar, 1 teaspoon of anise, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon of cloves.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and combine in large bowl with 1/2 cup melted butter, seasonings, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend well by hand.
Put into buttered casserole dish (large).
Mix 1/4 cup butter and corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: bridal punch
directions: Mix ginger ale and white grape juice together in equal parts. Freeze mixture of water and white grapes in ring mold. Can add food coloring to get a desired shade.

title: hash brown brunch casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; add 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Wash and drain kidney beans.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: taco soup
directions: In large pan, brown ground beef with onions. Drain. Adding one at a time, mix in chili beans, whole corn, hominy, Ro-Tel tomatoes, taco seasoning and Ranch dressing mix.
