Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally to avoid burning. Add creamed corn and simmer another 5 minutes. Serve over tortillas. Top with your favorite shredded cheese and sour cream.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, eggs, oil and water.
Add 10 ounce box strawberries (save 3 to 4 tablespoons of juice for icing). Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coated pecans
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff peak.
Add pecans and coat well.
Pour into melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir while baking.
Pour on wax paper and cool, then enjoy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix vanilla instant
pudding
with pineapple and juice. Pour in fruit cocktail;	add sliced bananas and add Cool Whip, enough to make look creamy.
Quick and easy!

title: tiger butter candy
directions: Melt white almond bark in microwave.
Stir in peanut butter. Line cookie sheet with wax paper and pour on it, spreading to edges.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle on top.
Swirl with tip of knife.
Put in freezer until firm.
Break into pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Combine milk and pudding in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon (about 15 minutes). Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir until smooth. Store in airtight container in refrigerator (3 cups pudding).

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown together.
Pour into a deep-dish casserole or pan (at least 4 qt.)

title: incredible hulk treat
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cool for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: hamburger potato pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until golden.
Add meat and seasoning. Cook until meat is lightly browned.
Add peas, tomatoes and catsup.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine mashed potatoes and eggs.
Spoon to form mounds over meat mixture. Add cheese on top (optional).
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated pork chops(grill; easy)
directions: *May omit if don't like.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar until creamy, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pie crust(makes 24 nine-inch pie crusts)
directions: Cut first
ingredients
together until well blended. Put corn syrup in quart jar and finish filling jar with water. Add to flour mixture; roll out.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together, saving enough crumbs to spread on top.
Bake at 350° until firm (20 to 30 minutes).

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz or Velveeta. Add cooked rice and cooked and drained broccoli. Place in casserole and heat at 300° until bubbly.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar and beat longer.
Beat eggs separate in another bowl.
Add to butter.
Pour flour over chopped fruit and rub well.
Then add to other mixture.
Cook on low heat until done.
Don't use all the flavor in each of the bottles.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 layers.

title: layered salad
directions: Break up lettuce into pieces in bottom of a large bowl.
Slice onion and celery thin and layer over lettuce.
Mix sour cream, sugar, Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Spread over lettuce.
Crumble bacon over the top and then sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to package directions.
Roll out for two 9-inch crusts; line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix ingredients well, batter will be stiff.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Cut into squares.
Good warm or cold.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix onion, cheese, eggs, milk, oil, creamed corn, bell and hot pepper (as much as you like); add meal and mix well.
Pour into greased hot skillet (two 8-inch.)
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until done.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt. Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out moisture. Add carrots and pepper.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mash potatoes. Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs. Cream well. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to lukewarm milk, then add to potato mixture. Add sifted flour to make a stiff dough. Toss on floured board and knead well. Put into a large bowl and let rise double in bulk. Knead slightly. Rub over top with melted butter; place in casserole. Cover tightly and place in refrigerator cabinet until ready to bake.

title: raisin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add other ingredients, except raisins and nuts.
Mix well, then add raisins and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Crust will be hard at first, but will soften up shortly.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Combine chocolate chips and all but 1 oz. of the almond bark in a 2 quart measuring cup.
Microwave on high for 2 to 4 minutes (until melted).
Stir once.
Stir in miniature marshmallows, peanuts and cereal.
Spread mixture on foil-covered 16-inch pizza pan.
Arrange cherries on top.
Microwave remaining almond bark in a cup on high for 1 to 2 minutes until melted.
Drizzle over pizza.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Let pizza stand at room temperature to set, or chill in fridge until firm.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: barley and laban(umheeah)
directions: In saucepan, add barley and enough water to cover. Cook till barley is soft.
Water will absorb.
Add to bowl of laban.
Add crushed garlic, salt to taste.

title: slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion, pepper and carrot.
Toss lightly.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and let cool.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over top of cabbage mixture and pour cool dressing over it.
Do not stir.
Let set overnight in refrigerator; toss lightly when ready to serve.
Be sure to cover, it smells.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift baking powder, flour and cocoa together 3 times.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with liquid, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Pour batter in 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Test after 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil and skin potatoes.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Oven fry eggs until over easy.
Chop pickles and onion.
Mix together all ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat
eggs;
stir
in sugar, salt and flour.
Add corn, light cream and butter.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2 quart dish. Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: chocolate peppermint pie
directions: Press the crust into a pie tin.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Then add all ingredients.
Grease. Heat a 13 x 9-inch pan real hot.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind all fruits together and mix with sugar.
Then mix Jell-O and water and add to cranberry mixture.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk in 1-quart casserole dish.	Stir in tuna. Add eggs, peas and milk.
Bake at
350° for 20 minutes. Top with potato chips and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken
in water with celery, bay leaf and sliced onion until done.
Remove chicken from bone.
Save stock.
Mix and bring to
boil chicken broth and soup.
Pour over chicken that has been placed
in
bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix pepper,
salt, flour, buttermilk and margarine.
Form a smooth batter.
Spoon over
chicken.
Bake
at
for
to 30 minutes.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Mix and bring to boil the sugar, salt, celery seed, vinegar and oil.
Pour over cabbage.
Cabbage and onion should fill 1/2 gallon container.
Pour over dressing and let set overnight.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or two pie pans.
Boil spaghetti.
Mix together butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Add to spaghetti.
Dump spaghetti into baking dish to make crust.
Brown ground beef and onion; add spaghetti sauce to ground beef.

title: mexican cornmeal muffins
directions: Mix well and bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: football special
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add beans, tomatoes, brown sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Set oven to 325°.
Pour milk over bread cubes; add salt and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to bread mixture along with butter, vanilla and raisins.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Set casserole in a large ovenproof pan.
Pour in hot water to 1-inch of top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until silver knife inserted near rim comes out clean.

title: longboy cheeseburgers
directions: Combine ground beef, pepper, catsup, corn flake crumbs, evaporated milk, salt, Worcestershire sauce and onion in a 2-quart bowl and mix well.
Cut 2 loaves of French bread in half lengthwise.
On cut side of bread, spread 1/4 of meat mixture, covering to edges.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake about 25 minutes at 375° or until meat is cooked to your liking.
During last 5 minutes, top liberally with grated cheese or cheese strips.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the pecans; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into a ball, and coat with pecans.
Makes 1 cheese ball.

title: mushroom shirred eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, onion and milk.
Spoon about 3 tablespoons soup mixture into each of 6 ungreased 6 ounce custard cups.
Break an egg carefully into each cup.
Mix butter, bread crumbs and salt; sprinkle on eggs.
Place cups on baking sheet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until eggs are done.
While eggs bake, heat slices of meat in oven.
Unmold eggs on meat.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onions; drain fat. Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: peachy punch
directions: Mix jello, sugar and 4 cups of hot water.
Stir until melted. Add almond extract, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir until well mixed.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale and stir.

title: eggs la strata
directions: Cut each piece of bread into 9 pieces.
Grate cheese. Sprinkle over bread.
Cook, crumble and drain sausage.
In a blender, place eggs, half and half cream and seasonings.
Blend. Pour over sausage and bread.
Cover it all set it in the refrigerator overnight.
In the morning bake it at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black walnut cake ii
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until very light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavoring and beat again.
Mix flour with baking powder.
Add alternately the flour mixture and the milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in walnuts.

title: french fried zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into strips.
Spread on paper towel; sprinkle with salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Pat dry with paper towel. Shake in paper bag containing flour, seasoned salt and pepper. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with more salt.
Serve hot.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Place chicken and broccoli in bottom of dish.
Spread soup on top.
Add a small amount of milk to soup.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple (including juice) and coconut in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Cover with slices of margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll into balls.
Bake in 350° oven on Teflon or greased pan for 20 minutes.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in sauce and taco mix; simmer for 5 minutes.
Unroll dough and spread on bottom and sides of 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes until golden.
Cover crust with meat; top with cheese.
Bake until cheese begins to melt.
Top with other ingredients.

title: braunschweiger pate
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Should be pudding consistency.
If too dry, add more Miracle Whip.
Spread on cracker or cocktail rye bread.

title: nacho cheese and beef soup
directions: In medium saucepan, brown ground beef; drain.
Add beef broth, picante sauce, cumin and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in soup. Heat gently, stirring frequently to prevent scorching.
Do not boil.
Pour into serving bowls; garnish with tortilla chips and sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream together until light butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat in one at a time.
Add buttermilk with soda.
Dissolve.
Mix in large bowl flour, chopped candy, pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: "grandma's raisin bran muffins"
directions: Mix together in large bowl or pot.
Put spoonfuls in a muffin tin and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Can be kept a couple of weeks in refrigerator and used as needed.
Best when mixed ahead and place in refrigerator overnight.
Can add extra raisins (optional).

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle rhubarb over top of unbaked cake.
Pour sugar over rhubarb.
Sprinkle cinnamon over sugar, if desired.
Pour cream over all and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake sides pull away from pan.
Cool and serve inverted with Cool Whip.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Place margarine in small bowl and, with electric mixer, beat several minutes until creamy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla, then milk, a little at a time, and beat well.
Tint portions of icing with food coloring to decorate.
Ice and decorate cake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
Easy to double recipe and make 4 pies at once.
You can freeze them.

title: light cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased skillet. Let rise a little.
Bake at 425° for about 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Add 1 tablespoon oil to wok or skillet and heat on high.
Add meat and stir until brown.
(I also add 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce to meat while cooking.)
After meat has browned, remove from heat and add vegetables and cook tender-crisp, then return meat to vegetables. Add soup.
Heat until boiling and serve on rice.
Cook rice according to directions.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Combine cheeses and spinach, stuff into cooked shells. Arrange in a greased 13X9X2-inch baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce over the shells. Cover and bake for 30 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 12-14 servings.

title: broccoli-cheese and rice casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and set aside to drain.
Saute the onion in butter until tender.
Add soups and Velveeta to butter and cook on low until cheese is melted.
Stir in cooked rice and drained broccoli.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Sift flour; measure and sift again with baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add to beaten egg and milk.
Stir in apples.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in oil or Crisco and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve and enjoy.

title: party cheese-nut ball
directions: In 1-quart bowl, combine cheese, mixing until well blended; add remaining ingredients except nuts and stir to combine.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate until mixture is well chilled, about 1 hour.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Heat milk, sugar and shortening in saucepan until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast and let stand about 20 minutes. Add beaten eggs and flour and beat until dough is smooth, but still soft, then knead lightly on floured board.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Grease 3 cake pans well with margarine; sprinkle bottoms generously with brown sugar and all nutmeats.
Divide dough into three parts, rolling each 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Spread generously with softened margarine and brown sugar.
Roll up as jelly roll and cut off 1-inch slices. Place in cake pans and let rise until double.
Bake about 25 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cherry coffeecake
directions: Beat the sugar, oleo, shortening, baking powder, vanilla, almond and eggs together on low speed until well blended.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Stir in 3 cups flour.
Spread 2/3 of batter in pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter by tablespoons onto pie filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze of powdered sugar and milk.

title: cherry tortilla desserts
directions: Bring the sugar, water and margarine to boil.
Set aside. Place 1 tablespoon pie filling on flour tortilla and roll up like enchilada.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour liquid mixture over "cherry" enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Liquid will be absorbed in cooking.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Add Cool Whip and blend completely.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: golden pork chops
directions: Cook pork chops in lot of oil until brown.
Pour oil off. Remove pork chops from skillet.
Combine soup and water in skillet. Heat to boiling.
Return pork chops in soup.
Cover and cook until chops are no longer pink.
Season to taste.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In bowl, mix together egg yolks, milk and lemon peel.
After mixing, add lime or lemon juice.
Mix for another minute.
Pour mixture into shell.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool before refrigerating. Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together, put in iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Slowly add (and cream) the sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well and add flour and vanilla.
Place cake in cold oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 285°.

title: dessert cake
directions: Bake and cool cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chilled summer tomato cucumber soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except the garnish in a blender. Blend until smooth.
Chill 1 hour (at least).

title: frozen dough
directions: Warm milk to lukewarm; add 4 tablespoons sugar and yeast.
Let rise until you get dough ready.
Mix flour, salt and butter as for pie.
Beat egg yolks and add to dough, then add yeast batter and beat until smooth.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, roll as for pie.

title: chocolate eclair torte
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with one layer of crackers.
Mix pudding and milk.
When pudding is set, fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half of pudding mixture on top of crackers.
Place another layer of crackers on top.
Spread remaining mixture over crackers. Place last layer of crackers on top.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.
Chocolate Sour Cream Frosting is great with this recipe.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: macaroni and cheese(crock-pot)
directions: Toss cooked macaroni in oil.
Add all remaining ingredients. Place in lightly greased crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir several times.

title: steak de burgo for two
directions: Mix together all ingredients except steak.
Pour over steak in flat casserole or pie dish; turn over.
Marinate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Grill to desired doneness.
Heat remaining marinade; serve with steak.

title: banana brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chips with margarine.
In large mixer bowl, beat chocolate mixture with Eagle Brand, biscuit mix, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in walnuts.
Place bananas on bottom of pastry shell.
Pour chocolate mixture over bananas.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into a buttered dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add chopped onion.
Pour slightly diluted milk over potatoes (enough to cover potatoes).
Pour a can of mushroom soup over all and bake about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender in a 350° oven.
The last 8 minutes add shredded cheese and bake until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: grace riordan's veggie pizza
directions: Some veggie combinations:
Cauliflower, black olives, red peppers and carrots or broccoli, yellow peppers, green olives and carrots.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Heat butter and oil.
Add garlic.
Add chicken.
Cook until chicken is brown.
Add rosemary, salt, pepper and wine.
Allow wine to bubble for 2 to 3 minutes, the lower heat to simmer. Cover pan; let simmer until done, approximately 30 to 35 minutes. Turn several times during cooking.
Watch carefully as it tends to brown quickly toward the end.

title: sweet 'n' sour brisket
directions: To make marinade, stir together vinegar, apple juice, chili sauce, brown sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Put meat and marinade in plastic bag and chill for 12 to 24 hours turning bag occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup; stir in oleo.
In bowl, beat eggs.
Add eggs to mixture.
Add vanilla, salt and pecans.
Mix flour and sugar; sprinkle over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour filling into shell.
Bake at 350° for glass or at 375° for metal pan for about 45 minutes, or until tester inserted halfway between the outside and center of pie comes out clean.

title: oatmeal coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 thin unbaked pie shells. Bake 1
hour in a 350° oven.
Let cool before serving.

title: cherry topped cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix in large bowl.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
(Mixture will be crumbly.)
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan 3/4 way up side of pan.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute; add slowly milk, vanilla and lemon.
Pour on top of crust and bake 45 to 55 minutes at 300°.
Cool and top with cherry pie filling or use blueberry.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: spareribs
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Add catsup, water, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and salt and pepper.
Cook ribs 1 1/2 to 2 hours in water.
Drain.
Broil about 10 minutes with sauce on.

title: overnight caramel cookies
directions: Mix together cake flour, brown sugar, salt, soda and cream of tartar, then add melted lard, but do not have hot.
Add eggs well-beaten; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Form into 4 to 5 rolls and let stand overnight in a cool place or refrigerator.
Slice thin and bake in moderate oven.
These are rich and crisp.
This makes about 2 gallon cookies.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine sugar and syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes. Syrup will be very hot.
Be careful.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Quickly pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store airtight.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease and dust pan with flour.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, allspice, soda and baking powder.
Add fruit and nuts and toss to coat.

title: coffee and cream
directions: Take hot coffee and place in blender.
Add sugar and ice cream.
Blend until thick and creamy, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour in cup.
Top with cinnamon and whipped cream (optional).
Serve with favorite cookies.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Put butter in bottom of skillet; add salt, onion and hominy. Add chili powder to taste and cook about 5 minutes.
Remove from fire; place in casserole with grated cheese on top.
Place in oven until brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan and bring to a boil. (Recipe may be doubled, if needed.)

title: roast beef barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Cook all day or at least 6 to 7 hours.
Add a little hot pepper for a spicy taste.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, put sugar, water, raisins, butter, cloves, carrots, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Simmer all together for 5 minutes, then cover and rest it for 12 hours.
This is very important.
The next day, add nuts, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Bake in two oiled loaf pans or one tube pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: prize-winning freezer dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand to cool and refrigerate for several hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt 2 sticks oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients; pour on top of melted oleo.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: swedish oatmeal bread
directions: Soften the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine oatmeal, molasses, shortening and yeast.
Add flour to make stiff dough, 1 cup at a time.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Let rise in greased bowl until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Divide the dough and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Put into greased pans and grease the top of the loaves.
Let rise until double, then bake at 350° for 40 minutes; makes 3 loaves.

title: craig's christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add egg yolks and beat. Next, add nuts and flour to mixture. Stir.
Chill mixture.
Form into small balls. Beat egg whites and put a dab on top of each cookie. Top with piece of cherry.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine everything but Tater Tots.
Put in casserole dish. Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are done.
Hamburger or chicken may be substituted for tuna.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans. Mix well. Chill at least 1 hour. Shape into a ball and coat with pecans. Yields 1 cheese ball.

title: meaty lasagna
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Cook meat and add Ragu sauce.
In a separate pot, beat eggs, cottage cheese and parsley.
Grease 12 x 14-inch baking pan.
Stir egg mixture.
Layer in pan as follows: thin layer of meat, layer of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, cheese and lots of meat.
Repeat layers.
Last layer is lots of cheese and meat.
Cover noodles with meat.
Put aluminum foil on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine butter and cheese, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Knead slightly.
Roll out, cut in desired size biscuits.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Pat corned beef in bottom of pan.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise.
Blend.
Add celery, pepper and onion.
Refrigerate.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, egg, flour, buttermilk and sugar if desired. Cover bottom of skillet with cooking oil and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Heat pan in oven, then pour cornbread mixture into hot pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Serve hot.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Add eggs, vanilla and pineapple.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: liz's stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cabbage and tomato sauce.
Add to mixture 2 tablespoons tomato sauce.
Place in pot the green leaves of cabbage.
Boil until tender.
Wrap cabbage leaves around small balls of meat and rice mixture until all meat mix is used.
Place in pot.
Chop remaining cabbage; pour over stuffed cabbage.
Add garlic and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 45 minutes, covered.
Add little water if needed.
Avoid excessive stirring.
Be sure cabbage mix does not stick.

title: canine cookies(for your favorite dog)
directions: Kids love to make them.
Dogs love to eat them!

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together.
Add graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Mix well and pat into a sheet pan.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will also need 1 Reynold's oven cooking bag (large size).

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, boil unpeeled potatoes until tender. Remove from water and allow to cool. Preheat oven to 350°.

Peel and slice sweet potatoes. In a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer potatoes, apples and pecans. Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nutmeg. Dot with butter. Pour apple cider over top. Bake 45 minutes.

title: no-fat spanish rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring broth to a boil over high heat. Add rice; reduce heat to low so rice bubbles gently.
Cook 50 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
While rice is cooking, combine garlic, onion, green pepper, celery and 3 to 4 tablespoons juice from tomatoes in a large skillet.
Saute over medium-high heat 5 to 7 minutes.
Add tomatoes and remaining juice; coarsely cut up tomatoes.
Stir in seasoning and honey; bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 10 minutes longer.

title: oven-easy baked rabbit
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dip pieces of rabbit meat in melted margarine, then roll in mixture of crumbs and salt.
Place pieces in greased shallow baking dish, but do not crowd.
Drizzle any remaining butter over pieces.
Bake, uncovered, until fork-tender, about 1 hour or longer.

title: philly 3-step chocolate lover's cheesecake(whip up this wonderful chocolate cheesecake in minutes!)
directions: Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Cooking time: 40 minutes.

title: sour cream
directions: Place in blender; mix until smooth and creamy.

title: scalloped potato and chicken bake
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika and thyme.
Reserve 2 tablespoons flour mixture.
Use
remaining
to
coat
chicken pieces.
Brown chicken on all
sides
in
butter.
Arrange
in center of large shallow
casserole.
Peel
potatoes
and
slice thinly.
Arrange layers
of potatoes around chicken, sprinkling each layer with dry onion soup mix and reserved seasoned flour. Pour any remaining drippings
from chicken over potatoes.
Pour boiling water over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: liver and onions
directions: Have liver sliced to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cook and stir onions and margarine in a 10-inch skillet until tender.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Heat 1/4 cup shortening in same skillet until melted.
Coat liver slices with flour.
Fry liver in shortening over medium heat until brown, 2 or 3 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add the onions during last minute of cooking to heat through.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in water. Mash them through a strainer, extracting all juices. Add juices to cabbage and lemon juice. Cook for 1 hour. Stir in sugar substitute, tomatoes, peppercorns and chicken broth.
Cook 1 hour longer.
Season with salt.
Serves 4.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and saute onion.
Add sauce.
Combine mixture with drained noodles.

title: apple-tomato relish
directions: Cut or chop fine tomatoes, apples, peppers, onions and celery, then add sugar, salt, mustard seed and vinegar.
Boil until quite thick (about 2 hours).
Ingredients can be ground, if desired.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix together; place into pie crust (9-inch).
Cover the edge of the crust with foil.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix crumbs with beaten eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Put flour in bowl.
Pour in 1 or 2 cups milk.
Put lard in and mix with the flour and milk.
When mixed, roll out with rolling pin and cut with cookie cutter.
Put in oven and bake until done.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken in heated oil until well browned.
Add salt and pepper as pieces of chicken are removed from skillet and set aside.
Now cook onions and garlic in same oil until tender.
Add white wine, tomatoes and thyme; simmer, scraping pan often.
Return chicken to skillet, cover and cook slowly until tender, about 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms which have been sauteed in butter.
Serve chicken on platter after pouring sauce on top.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spread into pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: summer salmon barbecue
directions: Tortillos, dipped in chili flavored tomato sauce, filled, rolled and covered with more sauce.

title: pineapple coconut chess pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Beat 5 minutes at high speed. Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 325° oven for one hour or until golden brown.

title: goody salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and cool.
Add remaining ingredients; refrigerate.
When thick, cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce.

title: broccoli-ham roll-ups
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and brown until smooth.
Add the cheese.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Cool. Slightly grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
If broccoli is in large bunches, separate stalks.
Roll slice of ham around stalk of broccoli, leaving the floweret end sticking out.
Place in baking dish, floweret end next to edge of dish.
Make 2 rows of rolls, side by side.
Pour thickened cheese mixture down the middle of rolls.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Cut oranges into pieces; remove seeds. Wash cranberries. Grind oranges and cranberries with food processor. (If you freeze the oranges and cranberries, it works best.) Mix well. Add sugar until mixed well.
Store overnight.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Put all ingredients into a pretty bowl or a suitable size brandy snifter.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: yellow cake or 2 jelly rolls
directions: Beat egg yolks until very light and lemon colored; beat in sugar gradually.
Add water (hot), beating constantly.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt and beat into egg mixture.
Bake in 3 well-greased layer cake pans at 375° for 30 minutes or make 2 jelly rolls.

title: connie's brunch orange drink
directions: Mix together and blend in blender for 30 seconds.
Serve in wine glasses.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup oats mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: aunt carrie's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 375° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel potatoes, cook tender.
Beat in eggs.
Mix all together. Pour in 3 pie crusts and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Mix sugar and flour together and stir into liquid ingredients.
Add coconut (save a little to sprinkle on top).
Fold beaten egg whites into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Spread sauerkraut in pan.
Sprinkle with rice, then the onion, then hamburg, salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and cook 45 minutes over low heat.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Rinse and drain chestnuts.
Cut strips of bacon in half. Wrap half strip of bacon around chestnut and fasten with a toothpick.
Place in a broiler pan (one that grease can drip through).
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Remove from pan and place in an ovenproof serving dish.
Combine brown sugar and ketchup and drizzle over chestnuts being careful not to drizzle on toothpicks.
Return to oven until sauce is hot and bubbly.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Add sugar to crumbs. Blend in melted oleo, coconut, peanut butter and nuts.
Mix well with your hands.
Shape into firmly packed balls.
Dip into chocolate mixture (melted chocolate bits and paraffin).
Put on cookie sheet covered with foil or waxed paper to harden.
Makes 75 walnut size balls.

title: franks in a loaf
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Split hot dogs lengthwise, not cutting completely through.
Fill each with cheese.
(Optional Filling: chili, relish, ketchup, etc.)

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Place ingredients in layers in an 8 x 8 x 3- inch pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: rice with vegetables
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms, green pepper and zucchini in olive oil.
Add tomato sauce.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in the rice; heat through for 5 more minutes. Serves 4.

title: blonde nut squares
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add the egg and vanilla; beat well.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chopped nuts and chocolate morsels.
Spread batter in a lightly greased 8 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares (about 1 1/2-inches).

title: railroad casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain, then simmer with other ingredients and bring back to a boil. Take off heat and make a thin cornbread topping to go over the beef and vegetable mixture in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes a meal in itself.

title: coal plant(do not eat)
directions: Place coal in a dish.
Drop some food coloring over it.
Mix other ingredients and pour over it.
Fun for kids to watch grow.

title: topping for pies
directions: Mix together and sprinkle on top of open face fruit pies. Bake pie as usual.

title: peppers and onions
directions: In large skillet, saute oil and garlic; add peppers and onions.
Good with sausages!

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, let sit at room temperature until it just begins to rise.
Roll out bread (use flour to help roll it out).
Put Provolone cheese in middle, then pepperoni, Mozzarella, chopped broccoli (thawed, not cooked), Colby cheese and top with Parmesan.
Pinch and seal ends to close.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until it is brown.

title: two-layer yellow cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients. Add milk; beat well. Use 2 (8-inch) layer pans. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crumb top for pies
directions: Blend the ingredients together with fork.
With your hand, grasp a handful of the mixture and form a ball.
Crumble the dough ball over your favorite fresh fruit or canned pie filling.
You must provide your own bottom crust.
Bake per the instructions of your pie.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in baking dish.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add juice and mix well.
Divide into three portions and roll out each piece.
Spread with soft margarine and sprinkle with mixture of nuts, cinnamon and powdered artificial sweetener to taste.
Roll and slice 1/4-inch pieces. Place cookies on sheet and bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add flour mixture and sour cream alternately.
Add vanilla and fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into a large greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is brown and springs back.

title: argo melting moment cookies
directions: In bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine until smooth.
Beat in flour mixture and vanilla until well blended.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: orange glory rolls
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan. Boil for six minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour this in two 9-inch round pans, or two 8-inch square pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften yeast with warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, salt and boiling water; mix well.
Cool to lukewarm by adding cold water.
Blend in eggs and the softened yeast.

Add flour gradually to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition. Knead until no longer sticky. Divide into thirds and roll on floured surface to 12 x 10 inches, brush with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut in 1-inch slices and place in pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Invert on serving plate allowing sauce to drain onto rolls.

title: very special carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, spices, salt and pineapple.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in a 375° oven 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cheese Icing.
Serves 12.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Beat all ingredients on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes.
Put into lightly greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Can be frosted with vanilla glaze.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll 12 inches long in foil, shiny side out.
Refrigerate 24 hours before baking.
Poke holes in bottom of foil and bake on rack with water underneath 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: oatmeal cookies "the best"
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Let stand for 1 hour covered in plastic wrap. Do not skip this step because it is the secret for delicious cookies!

title: pasta gratin
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add sausage; cook until brown.
Season with salt and thyme.
Add mushrooms, garlic and nutmeg; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain fat.
Add wine; increase heat and reduce until nearly dry, stirring with wooden spoon.
Add tomatoes; reduce until thick, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add pepper and parsley; set aside. Boil pasta in salted water until nearly al dente.
Rinse under cold water.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch quiche pan or pie dish. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with mixer.
Pour into plate. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.

title: bill's potato salad
directions: Drain the potatoes well and mash all ingredients except eggs and paprika while potatoes are still hot.
Chop 3 eggs and stir in with a spoon.
If mixture seems dry, add salad dressing until desired consistency is reached.
Slice the fourth boiled egg and spread around top.
Dust top with paprika.

title: jeri buck's chicken soup
directions: Skim fat off chicken broth and put in large pot.

Add mixed veggies, onion, kidney beans, elbow macaroni, basil and Mrs. Dash. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and chicken and bring to a boil again. Simmer 10 minutes. Better the second day!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: backwoods bean soup
directions: In saucepan, brown the meat and onion.
Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat. Stir occasionally.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: italian sausage sandwich
directions: Brown sausage, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add seasonings and pizza sauce.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Spoon in Hoagie buns.
Wrap in foil and bake on a cookie sheet 15 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix the sugar and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in pineapple.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to mixture, stirring until blended.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Top with frosting.

title: crab bisque
directions: Combine soups and blend.
Gradually add milk.
Add undrained crabmeat and salt.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly until just hot enough to serve.
You must stir while heating, for it scorches very easily.
Serve sprinkled with paprika and parsley.
Serves about 11 cups.

title: one crust pie shell(9-inches)
directions: Sift
flour
and salt together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until size of small peas.	Sprinkle water over mixture while tossing quickly with fork, until particles stick together. Form into smooth ball.

title: squaw corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well; pour into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown hamburger in margarine; drain.
Combine with other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: frango mint pie
directions: Mix chocolate wafers, sugar and butter in bowl.
Press into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Soften gelatin in 1 cup cold water in small saucepan. Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves, about 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks in large bowl.
Whisk gelatin mixture into egg yolks carefully to prevent curdling.
Stir in melted mints and liqueur until smooth.
Cool until slightly thickened. Whip the cream until stiff; fold into egg mixture.
Fold in chopped mints.
Refrigerate until beginning to set (10 to 15 minutes).
Turn into prepared crust.
Refrigerate until set, at least 1 hour.
Garnish with dollop of whipped cream and chopped nuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread about 1 cup of the sauce. Arrange a layer of uncooked lasagne noodles.
Top with sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing noodles into cheese mixture below.
End with lasagne noodles on top.
Pour remaining sauce on, making sure noodles are completely covered with sauce. Top with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: patrick's quick and tasty cheese snacks
directions: Put the 6 crackers on a paper plate and put the 2 pieces of cheese over the top.
There will be a little cheese hanging over the edge of the crackers, so break it off and spread it about, then put the cheese and crackers in the microwave for 25 seconds on High.
If you want, you can put salsa on it when it's out of the microwave.

title: mama's pasta fazui beans
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight; rinse and drain.
Place beans in a large pot.
Add flour and 3 tablespoons oil and shake until beans are well coated.
Add 2 quarts warm water and garlic. Cover and simmer for 1 1/4 hours.
Saute onion, celery and carrots in 2 tablespoons oil and butter in a large skillet, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and parsley; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Add water to prevent sticking, if necessary.
After beans have cooked 1 1/4 hours, remove 3 cups and set aside.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly, press into a 8 X 4 inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear, drain and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
It can also be cooked in other pans, whatever you prefer.

title: cherry nut pie
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Whip until fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk, beating until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well and stir in drained cherries and nuts.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: For sauce, mix tomato sauce, tomato paste, spaghetti mix and water. Add 1/2 of this to spinach. Mix Ricotta cheese and eggs. Layer in dish: sauce with spinach, lasagna noodles, remaining sauce and spinach, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese. Top with other 1/2 of sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Pour eggnog and milk into a bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Pour at once into pie shell.
Chill at least 1 hour. Garnish with whipped topping and sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add soup, milk, Cheez Whiz and broccoli.
Precook rice in salted water; add to mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach and brown rice casserole
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Mix egg, flour and cottage cheese and add to sauce along with spinach. Stir in rice, pepper, thyme and 1 tablespoon Parmesan.
Put in greased 12 x 8-inch pan and top with remaining cheese and sunflower seeds. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings, approximately 210 calories per serving.

title: herbed lentils and rice
directions: Combine broth, lentils, onion, uncooked rice, wine and seasonings.
Shred 1/2 cheese, add to above mixture.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2-2 hours, until lentils and rice are done.
Stir twice during cooking.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Melt cheese and butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour.
Stir in Krispies.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and press flat on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 75.

title: cottage cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, blend in other ingredients less 1 cup flour and the soda.
Let rise until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Work in the last cup of flour and soda until smooth. Bake at 300°
for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix together and roll the chicken pieces in the mixture.
In an electric skillet, heated to 375° to 400°, melt 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup shortening.
Cook until done.

title: peppermint patti brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13x9x2inch pan. In a large bowl, stir together butter, sugar, and vanilla. Add eggs & stir until well blended. Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder, and salt. Blend well. Reserve 2 cups batter. Spread remaining batter in pan. Arrange Peppermint Patties in single layer over batter. Spread reserved batter over Patties. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from sides of pan. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.

title: yellow squash st. tammany
directions: Saute onion and carrot in margarine until soft.
Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add salt and other ingredients, except for dry bread crumbs from stuffing mix.
Mix.
Layer vegetable mixture and dry bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until top crumbs are brown.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and add remaining ingredients. Pour into storage bowl and refrigerate.
Roll in a small ball. Place on your favorite small crackers and garnish with a strip of canned pimento.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli, peel stems and dice.
Break flowerette into small pieces.
Place in a large mixing bowl.
Thirty minutes before serving, add cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoned salt.
Mix thoroughly.

title: brownies
directions: Melt and cool chocolate.
Mix sugar, vanilla and 4 egg yolks. Add the chocolate and milk.
Add flour and vanilla.
Fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into large greased pan.
Bake at 350°.
When done, sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar or frost with icing.
Makes 36.

title: apple dumpling like cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with freshly cut apple slices (couple of layers).
Into the flour and sugar mixture, beat in 2 eggs.
Mix in oil.
Spread this mixture over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Soften butter. Mix in sugar, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix up real good. It is real thick. Might have to use hands to mix. Roll into balls and put toothpicks in balls, then chill.

title: wassail bowl
directions: In a large saucepan, bring cider and cinnamon stick to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except garnish) and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Garnish with clove-studded orange slices floating on top. Serve warm with individual cinnamon sticks.

title: grasshopper salad
directions: Place pineapple and juice in a large bowl.
Add pudding and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cool 1/2 hour before serving.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix first 4
ingredients.
Stir vigorously.
Crumbly in Blue cheese; gently blend in.
Serve with fresh broccoli, cauliflower, carrots or celery chunks.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Cover each single slice of ham with cream cheese.
Roll up as a jelly roll.
Slice in small 1/4-inch circles.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Okra may be rolled up inside of roll and sliced as stated.

title: frozen chicken salad
directions: Toss
together
chicken,
pineapple,
pecans
and salt. Blend together
cream (whipped) or Cool Whip and salad dressing.
Fold into
chicken
mixture.
Pour
into
a
quart pan. Place in freezer; when frozen, unmold, wrap in foil and return to
freezer or slice and wrap each slice individually in foil. Return to freezer.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Crumble meat over bottom of a 2-quart well-buttered casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Layer onion, potatoes and carrots. Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water and pour over ingredients in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into an 8 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top
with 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add milk.
Mix and pour into baking dish with butter.
No need to stir.
Add fruit evenly over top and sprinkle with more sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and chill. Take out enough dough each time to roll thin, but so as to be easy to handle. Do not handle the dough more than necessary, but use only enough flour on a board to pat into a ball and roll without sticking. Cover rolling pin with cloth to roll. Put a large spoon of filling on cookie and cover with another thin cookie. It is not necessary to press them together. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: june's okra to can
directions: Slice enough okra to fill a gallon jar and put into a pan. Cover with warm water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Boil one minute, no longer.
Take off heat and put into 2 quart jars and fill with broth from okra.
Seal with hot seals.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in greased dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl, stirring well. Cover tightly. Chill at least 8 hours. Serve over salad. Yields 4 cups.

title: fritos chili pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; stir in chili and beans. Alternate layers of Fritos and hamburger mixture in 12 x 9-inch dish until all are used.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: curried fruit
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in small saucepan, add sugar and curry powder.
Drain fruits (very well on paper towels). Layer in 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole with peach halves on top. Pour in butter mixture, place a cherry
in center of each peach. Bake 1 hour, uncovered.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Next day reheat at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best served with baked ham and made one day ahead of time.

title: cranberry banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in bananas, flour, soda and nuts.
Fold in cranberry sauce.
Pour into prepared pans and bake 60 to 65 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes under cold running water to prevent turning dark and place immediately in cold water.
Put large kettle of water on to boil and place potatoes in water.
Cover and cook until tender. Put in pan.
Pour melted butter over.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add marshmallows and brown and then serve.

title: mock baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Pour over cereal. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chips together and spread over cereal mixture. Put in refrigerator to cool. Cut into squares.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Layer in a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole 1/2 Velveeta, 1/2 tomatoes, 1 1/2 cans chili peppers, garlic salt and chili powder and 1/2 Cheddar.
Repeat layers, ending with Cheddar on top. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Cut in shortening.
Pour yeast mixture into flour.
Add 1 cup cold water (more if needed).
Work dough until rubbery.
Grease a large glass bowl.
Pour dough into bowl. Coat with shortening and cover with plastic wrap.
Let dough rise about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle flour on work area and work dough out. Roll out dough and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and allow to rise 30 minutes in a warm place.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: cherry angel delight
directions: Cut or tear cake into 1/2-inch pieces to measure 8 cups. Place half cake cubes in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 cup of pie filling; spread remaining filling over cake.
Top with remaining cake.
Spread pineapple over cake.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Spoon over cake.
Cover and chill. Cover top with Cool Whip and cut into squares.
Top each square with reserved cherries.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Take from freezer about 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli-rice bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Cook celery and onion in margarine.
Combine soup, water and cheese.
Combine with broccoli, rice, celery and onion.
Place into buttered 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: egg custard in blender
directions: Blend all ingredients for 30 seconds and pour into 9-inch greased and floured glass plate.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Makes it own crust.

title: spinach continental
directions: Let spinach thaw; drain well, then arrange in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat milk slowly with the 2 tablespoons of butter and American cheese until cheese melts.
Cool, then stir in well beaten egg.
Pour cheese sauce over spinach.
Saute garlic in the 4 tablespoons of butter until browned; add toast cubes and stir until they absorb the butter.
Drain toast cubes on absorbent paper and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Arrange over top of sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chili-egg puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium-size bowl, beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and butter; blend until smooth.
Stir in chiles.
Pour mixture into a well-buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 35 minutes or until the top is light brown and the eggs are set.

title: ba's cookies
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugars; add beaten egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, then oats, coconut and lastly the Rice Krispies.
Drop by scant teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Flatten each with fingers or "heel" of palm. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until nicely browned.
Remove quickly from baking sheet to cooling rack with spatula.

title: matzoh-chicken turnovers(yields 10 turnovers)
directions: Sprinkle matzoh with water and wrap them with a damp towel. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Grease Bundt cake pan.
Coat with powdered sugar.
Add nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and water.
Mix well and add cake frosting, mixing well again.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken poupon
directions: Combine in large bowl or plastic bag the mustard, water or oil, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Add chicken, mixing to coat. Place chicken in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done. If desired, garnish with lemon and fresh herbs.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter brownie pizza
directions: Prepare brownies as directed and bake. Allow to cool completely.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for chicken, in bowl.
Mix well.
Parcook chicken in microwave for 15 minutes.
Remove skin. Pour marinade over chicken.
Refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.
Turn often.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or on grill.

title: bonbon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Chill.
Roll in small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Put coconut on top before baking.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 14 minutes.

title: linguini salad
directions: Chop 4 tomatoes and place in a large bowl.
Add chopped onion, chopped cucumbers, chopped green chilies and the chopped parsley. Toss and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, cook linguini according to package.
Drain and add cold water to make it cold.
Drain thoroughly.
Put into large bowl; add tomato mixture and toss while adding salad dressing.
Put into a serving platter and top with crumbled Feta cheese.

title: belgian beef stew
directions: Cut beef into small cubes.
Place flour in a plastic bag.
Add beef cubes; toss until well coated.
Heat butter over medium heat in a heavy pot.
Add beef and brown well on all sides.
After beef is browned, add beer and soup mix.
Bring to a boil; lower heat to a simmer and cook.
Cover until beef is tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Cover raisins with water; let stand for 2 hours.
Drain. Drain pineapple.
Pare and dice apples.
Clean and shred carrots. Prepare jello according to package directions.
Layer fruits and vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cooled jello over all. Carrots will float.

title: batter baked pork chops
directions: Trim excessive fat from chops and season with salt and pepper. Beat egg and milk in a shallow dish.
Dip pork chops in egg mixture, then into corn flake crumbs.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Shape into little balls.
Flatten with fork, not too flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown your ground beef, then add rest of your ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: indian corn meal
directions: Dice onion, cheese and pepper and mix with other ingredients. Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and slice. Can be wrapped in foil and put in freezer.

title: curious cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Press half mixture in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes. Spread chocolate chips and pecans over mixture.

title: italian flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Place fish in a single layer in well buttered 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread sauce mixture over fish. Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven just until cheese melts.
Serves 8 with 288 calories per serving.

title: eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until foamy.
Slowly add liquor and sugar.
Let sit 1 hour.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg mixture, milk, cream and egg whites together.
Top with nutmeg; serve.

title: sweet pickle relish(can be halved)
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions and bell peppers in food processor. Pour into dish pan (metal) and let sit for 2 hours.
Squeeze juice out through colander.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and baking soda together.
Add raisins to dry mixture.
Cream sugar, Crisco and butter until smooth.
Beat eggs and mix with milk.
Add eggs and milk to sugar.
Combine with flour mixture.
Will be firm dough.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove souffle from package and cut in half.
Microwave in small bowl on medium heat 2 to 5 minutes.
Add bread crumbs to spinach.
Add thyme and salt.
May also add garlic, if desired. Chop the mushroom stems and add to spinach mixture.
Fill the mushroom caps with the mixture and then sprinkle with cheese. Place the caps around the sides of a microwavable baking dish. Microwave on Medium for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: *mititei(romanian chopped meat fingers)
directions: In a blender, combine garlic and water, chopping to make a paste. Add and blend together the beef stock, baking soda, salt and thyme.
Add to meat and mix thoroughly, kneading meat.
Form 1/3 cup of mixture into sausages the size of a finger.
Broil on all sides on grill.

title: aunt virginia's pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk and baking soda in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook until light brown or until it's to the soft ball stage on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add pecans, vanilla and butter.
Beat until mixture is not runny. Drop by tablespoonful onto a sheet of waxed paper.

title: butterscotch yum-yums
directions: Mix chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Remove and add chow mein noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool. Store in closed container.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: mini blinis
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg yolks and sugar until smooth; set aside. Take bread and trim off crusts.
Roll each slice with rolling pin until flat.
Drop heaping teaspoonful of cheese mixture on bread slices.
Spread over slice evenly.
Roll each slice in half and put on cookie sheet.
Melt butter and drizzle over roll-ups. Sprinkle generously with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: filled carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan. Set aside. Combine flour and cinnamon in a bowl. Set aside. Combine sugar, oil and egg in a large bowl.
Add vanilla. Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually beat in flour mixture; blend well.
Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: the original kentucky whiskey cake
directions: Soak cherries and raisins in bourbon overnight.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Stir in soaked fruit and bourbon.
Combine 1/2 cup flour with pecans.
Add remaining flour, nutmeg and baking powder; mix well.
Fold in egg whites, then floured pecans.
Pour batter into a greased 10-inch tube pan lined with greased brown paper.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 3 to 4 hours.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: gobbledy goop
directions: Mix ingredients together (in order) to insure blending.
Chill or freeze overnight.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and vanilla pudding; beat with mixer.
Add Cool Whip; stir well.
In a 9 x 13-inch oblong cake pan, layer graham crackers and pudding, ending with crackers.
Chill.
Top with frosting.
Store in refrigerator.

title: holly's delight
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oleo and nuts and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of a large container of Cool Whip.
Spread on first layer.
Cook 2 small packages of coconut pudding with milk.
Cook until thick, then cool.
Spread over other layers.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Wash and dry
chicken
well.
Heat
butter
over medium heat and saute
chicken
until
lightly
browned.
Remove from skillet and pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion and garlic; saute one minute.
Add
broth
and stir up any browned pieces from bottom of pan.
Blend in mustard and tarragon.

title: grand marnier dip
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt in a small saucepan and mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat, stir in Grand Marnier and let cool.
Beat whipping cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold in Grand Marnier mixture.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry supreme pie
directions: Add and blend all ingredients; spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, approximately 4 hours.
Place in refrigerator about 45 minutes before cutting.

title: crispy butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and confectioners sugar. Beat in egg whites and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Roll into 1-1/2 inch balls, then roll in sugar. Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12-14 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Remove to wire racks to cool. Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients except ketchup. Pour ketchup on top. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Take one stick of butter, cut it up and put in bottom of pan, then pour 3 to 4 cups apples (or more apples) on top of butter. Take the cake mix and sprinkle over top of the apples.
Put a little of the apple juice or water on that; then sprinkle some cinnamon on top.
Cut up 1 stick of butter and put on top of that, sprinkle crushed pecans over that.
Bake for about 30 minutes (or until done) at 350°.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and Wesson oil.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix thoroughly with other ingredients. Bake in oven preheated to 300° about 1 hour in large loaf pan (tube pan.)

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth, then add milk, vanilla and lemon juice; mix well.
Top with pie filling.

title: vegie salad
directions: Drain all liquids and mix vegies.
Boil the remaining ingredients.
Cool completely and pour over vegies.
Refrigerate. Will keep 2 weeks.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Add flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moist.
Add vanilla, bananas, walnuts and pineapple.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, saute mushrooms and onions lightly in 1/4 cup margarine.
Combine cornstarch, salt, pepper and milk until smooth.
Gradually add to mushroom-onion mix, stirring constantly.
Add Worcestershire sauce; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until smooth.
Add potatoes, carrots and green beans; toss until coated.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with parsley and 2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Spread evenly on top of casserole. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: carrot-rice bake
directions: In a saucepan combine carrots, water, rice and salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Do not drain.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese, milk, eggs, onion and pepper.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
Return to oven for about 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Cut into squares.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk well.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour half of pudding mixture onto crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over pudding and pour the rest of the pudding on top. Cut strawberries in half and place on top.
Chill.

title: elsie's chicken
directions: Boil chicken legs 10 - 15 minutes, drain.
Place in bowl or zip-loc bag and add spice liquid mix - marinate 4 - 6 hours.

title: egg noodle lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Add butter and toss to coat. In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Spread a fourth of the spaghetti sauce in an ungreased 5-quart slow cooker. Layer with a third of the noodles, a third of the beef, a third of the remaining sauce and a third of the cheeses. Repeat layers twice. Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or until cheese is melted. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Crush graham crackers; add half of Eagle Brand.
Melt marshmallows in top of double boiler with other half of Eagle Brand.
Add marshmallow mixture to cracker mixture.
Add other ingredients, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Press batter into 10-inch tube pan and chill thoroughly.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.
In the morning, pack into sterile jars and seal.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and both sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs. Mix baking soda, salt and 1/4 cup flour.
Beat into first mixture. Add the rest of the flour and mix well.
Drop by scant teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Decorate each cookie with a few M&M's.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecue sauce or marinade
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed in medium mixing bowl. For use as a marinade, marinate meats of 1 to 2-inch thickness for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours at room temperature, turning once.
For use as a barbecue sauce, brush meats or poultry frequently with this sauce during the cooking time.
This sauce may be stored 1 week in a covered jar in the refrigerator.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat cheese and soup.
Do not boil.
Add gelatin while warm. Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a large, oiled mold. (Or use 2 small ones.)
Chill.
Serve with plain crackers, raw vegetables, etc.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch pan which has been sprayed. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
No frosting needed.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add bananas, coconut and pecans.
Bake in layers or in Bundt pan at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes, 30 to 35 minutes for layers.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef, onions and drain. Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil. Simmer 30 minutes. Top with cheese.

title: noodle broccoli cheese soup
directions: Heat butter. Add onion and saute 3 minutes. Add broth and heat to boiling. Gradually add noodles and salt and continue to boil. Cook until noodles are tender. Stir in broccoli and garlic powder. Cook 4 to 10 minutes (until broccoli is soft).
Add cheese and stir until melted (slice by slice). Add milk and pepper, stirring constantly, until heated.
Serves 8 to 10.
Cook/preparation time: 30 minutes. Serve with bread.
This soup is great reheated.

title: no fat strawberry cake
directions: Crumble up the angel food cakes into large bowl; set aside. Mix jello according to directions.
When jello begins to thicken, mix frozen strawberries and Cool Whip with jello.
Then pour mixture into bowl with angel food cake.
Place in cake pan and refrigerate.

title: corn	bread recipe
directions: Grease baking dish. Work it up with buttermilk so you can handle it. Make the dodgers. I make it with my hands and it will cream fluffy if you work it long enough. That makes it light and fluffy and I have a pan of warm water to wet my hands, which makes them smooth. I have the oven at 500°.

title: mimi's spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix into large portion of mixture.
Pour into greased pan. Top with smaller 1 cup mixture saved back for topping. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Remove skin and bone from chicken.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken into butter; then into mixture of 4 dry ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: cherry-pecan bread
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Set aside.

title: oil and vinegar chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
You may have enough batter for some cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or maybe longer.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream. Slice bananas.
Layer in large bowl the pudding, wafers and bananas. Cool in refrigerator.

title: mother's quick and easy chocolate sauce
directions: Mix these (except vanilla) together and, while stirring, melt over a slow heat.
If it boils, the sauce will form a shell on the cold ice cream and that's not all together bad.
Take off the heat when melted and stir in vanilla.
Spoon over ice cream and enjoy!

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup of milk in bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Beat with wire whisk until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 4 hours, until set.
Top with additional whipped topping.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Wash rice; add to 1 quart boiling salted water.
Do not stir. Cook, covered, for 40 minutes or until rice is fluffy and the liquid is all absorbed.
Mash sausage meat and fry for 15 minutes. Pour off and discard fat.
Add sausage to the rice.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix with 1/2 cup evaporated milk and melted stick of margarine.
Spread half of mixture in greased cake pan and bake for six minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/2 cup milk and spread on top of baked cake.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips and pecans, then rest of cake.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given and pour into lightly greased baking dish.
I use the 1 1/2-quart Pyrex.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sour cream softies
directions: Measure flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Cream butter with sugar and beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: cheeseburger chowder
directions: Brown beef.
Add celery, onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Blend flour and salt.
Add crushed bouillon cube and milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick (approximately 1 hour).
Add cheese.
Cook and stir only until cheese melts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: crunchy chicken or cutlets
directions: Remove skin from thighs.
Remove bone and fat.
Pound meat thin, wet chicken.
Mix corn flakes, paprika and pepper in plastic bag and crush.
Coat chicken, place on large shallow pan.
Pour oil on top of each piece.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop up artichoke hearts.
Mix with cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and garlic salt.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted. Serve as dip with crackers or chips.
