title: spaghetti the hard way (but worth it)
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet and drain.
In a large Dutch oven, heat oil and cook onion and bell pepper.
Add meat and garlic.
Add tomatoes (sauce, paste and crushed).
Add 2 cups water and mushrooms.
Add spices, except sugar, and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 4 hours.
Add sugar and continue to simmer 30 minutes.
When simmering, check and stir frequently.
Add water when necessary.
Remove bay leaves and serve over pasta.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup pasta sauce and 1/2 cup cheese.

title: peaches-and-cream tart
directions: For crust, crumble macaroons (about 2 cups).
In a large bowl, stir together macaroon crumbs, pecans and margarine.
Press mixture onto bottom and up sides of an 11-inch tart pan with a removable bottom.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, melted margarine, vanilla, milk and egg together.
When ingredients are well mixed, add flour gradually. Roll dough out on cookie sheet, adding more flour if dough is too sticky.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Bake in oven on greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 6 minutes.
Cookies are done when they get light brown on the edges.

title: baked croissant chicken casserole
directions: Roll out 1 tube of croissant rolls.
Use 4 squares instead of 8 triangles.
Pinch seams together on the 2 triangles to make the squares and separate dough to make the 4 squares.

title: riz biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll out and cut.
Place on greased pan and allow to rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry apple cake
directions: Peel apples; chop and set aside.
Blend together sugar, oil, orange juice, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to the creamed mixture. Add apples, nuts and cranberries and mix well; do not beat, just stir.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Frost with:

title: easy cherry cheesecake
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk, lemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill 4 hours.

title: venison roast
directions: The night before, place venison, salt, pepper, garlic salt and water in crock-pot.
Cook all night on low.
Next morning, add vegetables and cook on low until tender.
About 30 minutes before serving, remove soup stock to saucepan.
Add flour, cook to thicken.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cook on low until ready to serve.

title: squash souffle
directions: Combine squash, onion, sugar and salt.
Simmer with small amount of water for 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Mash with potato masher.
Add eggs, margarine, flour, milk and cheese.
Add seasoning salt to taste.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish for 30 minutes.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake for 10 minutes or longer if necessary.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Stir in next 4 ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine all except nuts and parsley.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Combine nuts and parsley on waxed paper.
Shape salmon mixture into ball and roll in nut mixture.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: scallop skillet
directions: Put cornstarch and salt in small bowl, combine with broth and soy sauce. Set aside.

title: turkey waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Fold in turkey, apples and celery.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, sprinkle walnuts over top.

title: tuna cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Put cream cheese in a bowl and mash smooth with a fork.
Add tuna, flake and mix with cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix until well blended. Refrigerate.
Serve with chips or veggies.
Also good as spread for sandwiches.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place unopened can of milk in pan on its side.
Cover with water.
Put lid on pan.
Bring to a boil.
Turn burner down so water will barely boil.
Boil for 5 hours.
Take can out of water. Let cool before opening.
Open and spread in pie shell.
Cool in freezer for a short time.
Spread with Cool Whip.

title: fresh apple date cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, salt and juice.
Add flour, soda, apples, dates and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake in a preheated slow oven (325°) for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: choc-o-dot cookies
directions: Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Stir in chips and nuts. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 360° for 8-9 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare 2 cups of elbow macaroni.
Drain and put in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Shape beef mixture into about 3 dozen tiny meatballs, using about a teaspoonful of mixture for each one.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400° or until brown.
It is not necessary to turn meatballs as they bake.
Insert a toothpick into each.
Serve with hot barbecue sauce.

title: squaw corn
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Drain off drippings.
Break eggs into measuring cup or small bowl and beat lightly.
Add to bacon along with corn, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until eggs are done.
(Only takes a few minutes.)

title: angel food cake
directions: Put sugar, water and pineapple in top of double boiler and bring just to boiling point.
Add cornstarch and flour which have been measured together and cook until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla when cool and fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour mixture into pie shells or graham cracker crust.
Spread Dream Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: spanish chicken with rice
directions: Brown chicken in Wesson oil or Crisco oil.
Add onion, pepper and rice.
Cook a little than add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except 7-Up.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes, until softened.
Stir in flour.
Add pumpkin, mashing it into a puree.
Add chicken broth, vermouth and salt.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add ginger and nutmeg.
Combine egg yolks and heavy cream.
Stir into soup.
Heat until hot but not boiling.

title: spicy cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper.
Combine with remaining ingredients and chill.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening. Stir in cocoa and sugar. Beat in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Divide into 2 greased pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello according to box directions.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: pea business
directions: Grease casserole and make a layer of hamburg using the whole pound.
Salt and pepper well.
Add a layer of sliced onion.
Slice 2 potatoes and season.
Add carrots and season.
Pour in the peas, juice and all.
Top with the remaining potatoes.
Fill casserole half full with water and top with dabs of butter.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use fresh, medium cucumbers.
Wash and cut into sticks.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers and let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain and pack into clean jars.
Mix solution.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers in jars. Put lids and rings on jars. Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix flour, soda, sugar, milk and raisins together.
Pour into cake pan.
Mix butter, brown sugar and water together in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over batter and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar together.
Add the oil, vanilla and zucchini to the eggs and sugar.
Combine the dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Sift all together and add to top ingredients.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Mix well.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sugar-top oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix together flour, rolled oats, brown sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
In small bowl combine egg, milk and cooking oil. Add egg mix to the flour mix, stirring just until moistened. Stir in walnuts.
Store tightly covered in the refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: honey oatmeal bread(2 loaves)
directions: Combine boiling water, oats, honey, margarine and salt.
Stir until melted.
Add sour cream.
Cool until lukewarm.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Add yeast, eggs and 2 cups flour to oat mixture. Beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rest 20 minutes.
Divide in half, shape each half into a loaf. Place each in a greased loaf pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
When ready to bake, remove from refrigerator 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on racks.

title: rolls
directions: Mix sugar, hot water and fat; let cool.
Add yeast and cold water, salt, flour and eggs.
Keep in icebox until about two hours before baking time.
Make rolls and let rise.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat a large heavy dry pan over high heat.
Slice sausage into bit size pieces and brown.
Remove sausage from pan with slotted spoon and reserve drippings for next step.

title: fried fish country style
directions: To prevent curling, score each piece of fish on ends with a sharp knife, about an inch between each cut.
Wash, then pat dry excess water, using a paper napkin or towel.
Season each piece lightly on both sides with a mixture of seasoning salt and pepper.

title: crunch candy
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave and add rest of the ingredients; stir well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto buttered wax paper.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain.
Brown ground beef, onion and celery in butter.
Combine with other ingredients and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls out on cookie sheet and bake as directed on package; cool.
Mix mayo, cream cheese and Ranch mix.
Spread on cooled rolls.
Top with chopped vegetables, usually 1 cup each of carrots, tomatoes, broccoli, celery, cauliflower, etc.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch dish and top with Stove Top stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: honey roasted nuts
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line pan with foil and grease foil. In saucepan over medium heat, combine honey, butter and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Put nuts into medium bowl. Pour honey mixture over nuts and stir until evenly coated.
Spread on prepared foil-lined pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until nuts are glazed and lightly browned.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and remaining cinnamon.
Toss with glazed nuts to coat. Makes 4 cups.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add green chiles and mushroom soup.
Mix well and heat.
In a 4 or 6-quart round casserole, place a flour tortilla, then a layer of the meat mixture, then cheese. Continue layering in this order, ending with cheese.
This can be heated in the oven or microwave.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat in cast-iron skillet about 2 tablespoons oil. While that is heating, mix all ingredients together and pour into hot skillet. Put in oven and bake at 425° until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Prepare vegetables and let stand.

title: mrs. winklers rolls
directions: Combine egg, sugar and oil.
Add to yeast and water mixture. Add 3 cups self-rising flour or enough to make a soft dough. Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each roll in melted butter and fold into pocketbook rolls.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for about 8 minutes or until done.

title: orange-date-cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour and baking soda.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately. Add pecans, dates and orange slice mixture.
Add coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 hour or until firm.
Remove from pan and pour glaze over.

title: george washington's christmas nog(about 4 quarts)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar gradually and beat until light and lemon-colored.
Add 1 cup liquor mixture, a drop at a time, beating slowly.
Stir in milk and half and half or cream.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks and fold into egg yolk mixture.
Chill.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; rinse and drain.
In skillet over low heat, cook sausage and onion until browned; drain. In mixing bowl, toss together noodles, sausage, onions, mushrooms, olives, 1 3/4 cups Cheddar cheese and pizza sauce.
Pour into casserole; bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until cheese melts and casserole is heated through.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and remaining Cheddar cheese for last 10 minutes of baking.

title: peanut butter 'n choco fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa in 2-quart microwavable bowl.
Combine sugar mixture, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and salt; add butter. Microwave 2 to 4 minutes on High until heated through.
Stir until smooth.
Pour immediately into well-greased 8-inch pan.
Chill. Cut into squares.
Place in well fitting lid container, store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring mashed strawberries, cornstarch and sugar to a boil. Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in lemon juice and halved
strawberries.
Pour in baked pie shell and chill.

title: mexican hamburgers with beans
directions: Chop, dice and shred all condiments. Heat chili and beans on medium heat. Grill hamburger patties to desired doneness. Warm tortillas. After hamburgers are cooked, place one pattie in a tortilla folded on a plate inside the fold; add beans. Smother with green chili and generously sprinkle on cheese. Add desired condiments and serve with Spanish Rice.

title: mexican salad(microwave)
directions: Spread meat evenly in 2-quart glass casserole.
Cook, uncovered, 4 minutes, stirring once, and drain.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add drained beans.
Cook 3 minutes.
Toss together in salad bowl the lettuce, tomato, avocado, green onions and cheese.
Add enough dressing to coat well.
Toss in chips and hot meat mixture.
Sprinkle with taco or Tabasco sauce.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Slice apples in quarters.
Melt caramels.
Add Eagle Brand and combine until smooth.
Dip apple slices into the caramel dip.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Pick over crab meat carefully and remove any bits of shell. (Drain canned crab.)
Mix all ingredients together except paprika and place mixture in a small baking dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake in a 300° oven until heated through.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: thursday casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Brown hamburger until pink color is gone.
Drain macaroni and put in large casserole. Add hamburger and spaghetti sauce.
Add cheese cut in small chunks, mix well.
Microwave for 15 minutes or in oven 20 minutes. Peppers and onions may be added to the hamburger if desired. Serves 8.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: One recipe will fit into the blender.
Blend all ingredients for 1 minute.
Add coconut after blending.
For a 9 x 13-inch pan you will need to double (make it twice) the recipe.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortellini chicken salad
directions: Cook veggies per package until crisp; drain.
Cook tortellini and rinse in cold water.
In large bowl combine all.
Toss to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain and mash.
Add all ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Cool.
Place in greased casserole and dot with butter.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: sweet potato party log
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over medium heat until very thick (about 10 minutes), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and allow to cool completely before proceeding.
When cool, beat in mixer at high speed for several minutes to make smooth. Add coconut and cornflakes to the mixture until consistency is right to handle.
Shape into 2 logs on waxed paper and allow to chill in refrigerator.
Blend cream
cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together. Spread on chilled logs as an icing.
Roll in chopped nuts and refrigerate until time to serve to make slicing easier.

title: pannukakko(oven pancake)
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or oleo and add 1/2 of this into batter. Put remaining butter in heated large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Pour batter over butter and bake in hot oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: cream cheese herb dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese until softened, adding herbs.
Roll
in chopped, fresh parsley.
Keep rolling batter until it becomes a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: new orleans king's cake
directions: Sprinkle yeast and 2 teaspoons sugar over lukewarm water.
Let soften.
Stir, then let sit about 10 minutes, until light and bubbly.
Mix 3 1/2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and nutmeg well.
Add yeast mixture, milk and lemon peel.
Work mixture together well.
(An electric mixer is fine for this.)
Add egg yolks and beat in well.
Work in 1/2 cup butter and continue to beat until butter is incorporated and mixture is smooth.

title: bishop's chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and pudding and beat until a little thick.
Fold in 2 cups vanilla ice cream (softened a little).
Pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with 1 chocolate bar (shaved with potato peeler).
Double recipe = 3 pies.
Will freeze well.
Allow to thaw slightly before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add salt. Beat eggs, then add to rest. Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, eggs and crumbled bread; spread mushroom soup across and top with cheese. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients except coconut for 3 minutes on low speed in blender.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Let stand for 5 minutes (when mixture separates).
Sprinkle with coconut and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: dorito's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast; layer bottom of casserole dish with Doritos. Mix chicken, soup, Ro-Tel and onion; pour over Doritos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 4 cups flour, sugar, dissolved yeast and salt.
Heat milk, butter and water until warm.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover; let rise until double, 10 minutes or more.
Keep in warm place out of draft.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and soft butter.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs together. Pour over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in dish with 1 small sliced onion.
Add 1 cup uncooked rice, 1 can mushrooms and 1 can beef consomme soup (bouillon cubes).
Stir in 2 tablespoons pimento (optional).
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon chestnut bites(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and brown sugar.
Heat.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef and 1/2 cup of the onion in skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.

title: dill dip
directions: To reduce calories and fat, use no-fat sour cream.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Pierce steak all over deeply with a fork; place in shallow non-metal dish.
Make marinade.

title: fruit topping(used for dipping fruit)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan and cook over medium-low heat until thick.
Stir constantly.
Don't let this burn.
Cool. Add cream (whipped) before serving.
Dip strawberries, fresh pineapple, apples, grapes, etc. into topping and enjoy.

title: orange candy
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixed ingredients, except powdered sugar, in a pan and bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Take out and stir; put back for 30 minutes.
Take out and beat in powdered sugar.
Drop onto wax paper by the spoonful.
Store in an airtight container.

title: pierzchala
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir together with egg and milk mixture.
Add salad oil.
Fry in hot oil (drop by teaspoon); drain and cool.
Put some sugar in a paper bag; shake cooled Pierzchala in the bag to coat.

title: easy cheese blintzes
directions: Cream egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Set aside. Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup (1/2 can) evaporated milk.
Mix cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup milk and pecans.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust.
Pour caramel mixture on chips.
Dab the remaining cake mixture over caramel layers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jackpot
directions: Cook rotini to package directions.
Saute ground beef and onion together.
Drain fat.
Add salt, chili powder and pepper. Add soup, tomato sauce, rotini, beans and 1/2 cheese.
Mix well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle or spread remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Good, good, good!

title: welcome wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheeses.
Add garlic, parsley, chives and flour.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Chill.
Slice and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all together.
Grease and flour pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: homemade cheese
directions: Put this in a bowl for a day or two.
Skim cream off of the top, then let milk turn to clabber.
Put in a large pot and heat until it feels warm to touch, then strain it in a flour sack. Hang on line and let it drip dry.

title: low country boil
directions: Fill a large pot with enough water to cover all ingredients. Add crab boil and heat until boiling. Adjust crab boil to suit your taste. When boiling, add potatoes and sausage.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes. Add corn and cook for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 3 minutes. Drain and serve. Serves 6.

title: pork chop and squash casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in 1/4 cup oil. Remove pork chops from pan. Into the same oil, add sliced squash, chopped bell peppers, chopped onion along with salt and pepper. Cook until tender.
Place vegetables into bottom of a large baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Pour small can of tomato puree over all the pork chops. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Mix in Ragu, water, oregano, salt and sugar.
Simmer.
Slice cream cheese into small slices.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, grease bottom.
Then add 1/3 of the sauce for the bottom layer.
Next, add a layer of uncooked noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Add 1/3 of sauce and cover with noodles.
On top of these noodles, add sliced cream cheese, then Mozzarella cheese and Mozzarella cheese again.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Let it set for 15 minutes before serving.

title: cape cod dressing and salad
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and serve over greens to which shredded red cabbage, strawberries and walnuts have been added.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in sugar gradually.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Bake in a well-greased Bundt pan at 325° to 350° for 50 minutes.

title: low-fat rice pudding
directions: In large heavy saucepan, combine milk, rice and raisins.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, about 20 minutes, stirring often until rice is almost tender.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, whisk egg, egg whites, sugar and evaporated milk until blended.
Gradually add egg mixture to rice mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium-low heat about 5 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into shallow 6-cup dish. Serve warm or cold sprinkled with nutmeg.
One-half cup serving has 190 calories (2 grams fat, 30 mg cholesterol).

title: beef brisket
directions: Crisscross heavy-duty aluminum foil in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Season both sides of meat with Accent, Lawry's seasoned salt, sliced onion and parsley flakes.
Place brisket in foil with fat side up.
Wrap loosely and cook for 4 hours at 325°.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
After measuring put into blender in small amounts and blend until it's powder.
Mix together all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make rounded teaspoon-sized balls.
Put 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 110 to 150 cookies.

title: party cheese
directions: Blend
all ingredients.
Store in a cheese crock.
Will keep in	the refrigerator for 3 weeks.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: "esther saners" apple cake
directions: Blend together first four ingredients, then add margarine.
Mix together until fine.
Beat egg with cold water and mix with fork. Put all ingredients together; mix until dough is formed.
Press with fingers into cake sheet.
Cut apples into 1/8 pieces and place into rows on dough.
Mix and sprinkle over apples, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and a little nutmeg.
Dot with a little butter or margairne.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in broccoli, ham and rice. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over casserole. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, mustard and salt.
Pound into steak on both sides. Brown meat, then cover with onions, carrots and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with sauce, brown sugar and more seasoning, if desired.
Cover pan and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
This recipe works well in a crock-pot also.

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and rinse with water.
Mix cottage cheese, Ricotta cheese, salt, pepper, chopped onions and egg.
Fill shells with cheese mixture.
Place on top of hamburger mixture in a glass pan. Mix tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Pour evenly over top of shells. Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake at 450° about 1 hour.

title: prune ribbon bars
directions: About 3 hours to 2 weeks ahead, heat prunes and 1 cup of water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes. Drain well.
In blender on high, put prunes, honey and lemon.
Do not peel.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Grease medium size dish.
Press crescent rolls to cover dish (sides too).
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: creme brule
directions: Scald cream slowly in microwave until there is a light film on top.
Set aside and cool to room temperature.
Lightly beat egg yolks, sugar, vanilla and cognac in a mixing bowl.
Whip egg yolk mixture slowly into cooled cream.
Place small baking ramekins in a casserole filled with 1/2-inch very hot water.
Pour custard into ramekins.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm but not solid, about 20-30 minutes.
Under cooking or over cooking is not a major hazard...just don't cook it until it is solid and definitely not until it is brown on top.
Remove ramekins from pan and cool. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, sprinkle brown sugar across the top of each one.
Place ramekins in pan and surround with ice cubes.
Put under broiler just until sugar is caramelized.

title: zesty grilled potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until done.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Put in casserole and marinate with dressing for a couple of hours. Grill until brown.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Boil together and pour over batter of cake.
Cook 20 mins. at 375° or until done.

title: grilled pheasant
directions: You will need bamboo skewers.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, cream butter, peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar together thoroughly.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Beat in orange juice.
Shape dough into a roll 1-inch in diameter and 7 inches long.
Wrap in clear plastic wrap.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Reshape into round log if necessary.
Slice cookies 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Place half the slices 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread center of each cookie with about 1 teaspoon of peanut butter.
Cover with remaining slices.
Seal edge with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on rack.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into small pieces and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Cook and drain sausage.
Add to dish.
Add cheese (reserving some for top), eggs, salt and mustard.
Pour over mixture in dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (can be made the night before and put in refrigerator).

title: cookie dessert
directions: Put the crushed Oreo cookies and oleo in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze for 1/2 hour.
Spread the ice cream over crushed Oreos and refreeze.

title: tricolored-peppercorn encrusted salmon
directions: Cut salmon into filets removing all bones.
Coat saute pan with olive oil.
Rub salmon with salt.
Crack pepper and place in side dish.
Coat one side of salmon filets with pepper; sear in saute pan on each side.
Place salmon and shrimp in shallow baking pan in 350° oven; bake for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Place fish in pool of sauce and top with shrimp.
Garnish if desired.

title: italian casserole
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium-high, cook ground beef and onion about 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, basil, oregano leaves, sugar and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes more to blend flavors.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, spoon 1/3 of meat mix; arrange 1/2 of potatoes on top.
Repeat layering, ending with meat.
Cover tightly with foil; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove foil; sprinkle mixture evenly with Mozzarella cheese; bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes for easier cutting.

title: o'henry bars
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, melt sugar and corn syrup (approximately 2 minutes on High).
Add peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Pour peanut butter mixture over rice cereal; mix well. Spread this in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In microwave-safe bowl, combine both types of baking chips and melt in microwave.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Chill until bars are set; cut into squares.

title: german egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs with salt.
Add enough flour to be able to knead dough.
Roll on floured board until very thin.
Dry and cut to desired width.
Cook in boiling broth with lid on pot for 20 minutes.
Be sure to have enough broth to cover noodles while cooking.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate (trifle) dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed, cool.
Crush heath bars.
Layer in bowl starting with cake, crumbled up, add a layer of pudding, then Cool Whip, then candy.
I refrigerate my pudding to cool somewhat, before spreading in over cake, then refrigerate over night.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix wet ingredients then dry ingredients and combine and mix until creamy texture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into balls the size of a nickel.
Roll in extra powdered sugar.
Dry on a cookie sheet. Store in tin boxes or cans.
Better with age.
Makes about 60.

title: fat-free bean salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill.
This salad is colorful and tastes great!

title: mexican pepper pie
directions: Pour Doritos into baking dish.
Mix soup, etc., and pour over chips.
Grate cheese over top and bake until bubbly (about 20 minutes at 325°).

title: mother's goulash
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Peel and dice carrots; boil in water until tender.
Brown onions, hamburger and celery in oil until done.
Combine all other ingredients (carrots and noodles should be drained).
Tomatoes should be cut up into small pieces.
Do not drain.
Simmer to blend flavors.

title: quick quiche
directions: Combine cheese and flour.
Sprinkle into pie shell. Top cheese with ham.
Combine eggs, milk and onion soup mix and pour over ham and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: double-delight cherry dessert
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Spread in
a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly over the top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Prepare glaze of sugar, milk and vanilla.
Drizzle over cake.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix jello like directions.
Add drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows into jello.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: "miriam's" chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and set aside to cool.
While cooking, mix flour and enough water to make stiff as a ball of pizza dough.
Cover and let set until ready to roll as thin as you can, using enough flour so they will not be sticky.
Cut in strips and drop into boiling broth.
When chicken is cool, separate from skin and bones and set aside until dumplings are about cooked.
Put chicken in and let it all get hot again and eat.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bottom Layer: Bake rolls at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes in 9 x 13 cake pan or cookie sheet. Cool.

title: paw paw's garlic pasta
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil; remove and drain.
Add butter and sliced onions; brown.
Add mushrooms and white wine; cook slow, covered. Bring water to boil; add pasta.
Cook on high.
Stir often until desired texture; drain.
Add browned garlic and olives to mushroom and onions.
Pour 1/2 mushroom/onion/oil over pasta. Toss and add fresh parsley.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time. Sift flour with baking powder; add alternately with milk and flavorings.
Place in greased pan in cold oven.
Set oven at 325° and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Do not open door while baking.

title: spam surprise
directions: Put chicken soup and Spam in a frypan, heating until mixture is warm.
Boil macaroni in saucepan until done.
Pour macaroni into Spam and chicken soup mixture.
Mix together and heat for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix in eggs, bananas and oil.
Add sugar and mix.
Put into a greased and floured oblong bread pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes for 1/2 recipe.

title: german pizza
directions: In skillet, brown beef with onion, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Remove meat from skillet.
Reduce heat to low and melt butter.
Spread potatoes and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Top with beef mixture.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over all. Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and melt.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add to rice.
Mix soup and milk and add to rice mixture.
Add mixture to the broccoli.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma's pie crust
directions: Cut together flour and shortening.
Add salt and sugar.
Break egg in measuring cup; add enough water to make 1/2 cup of liquid. Mix egg with flour mixture.
Roll out on floured covered board. Makes enough for 1 double crust and 1 single crust pie.

title: diet soup
directions: Cut all vegetables into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients. Cover with water in larger pot.
Boil 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together. Pour into casserole dish. Bake for 45 minutes. Do not burn.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown your hamburger and drain the fat.
Add green beans and tomato soup.
Put mixture into casserole dish. Add potatoes with ice cream scoop on top of mixture.
Place cheese on top of potatoes.
Put in oven at 325° until the cheese melts, approximately 15 minutes.

title: microwave sweet-sour turkey loaves
directions: In 1 3/4-quart casserole, combine sweet-sour sauce, 1/4 cup catsup, green pepper and peaches.
Set mixture aside.
In medium mixing bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon catsup, soy sauce, ginger, garlic powder and pepper.
Add turkey and mix well. Shape into 4 loaves.
Arrange loaves in casserole.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on High power, covered, until done.
Turn casserole 1/2 turn once.

title: barbecue wing dings
directions: Cut off the small piece of chicken wing and the two bone part so you have only the meaty part.
Mix the ketchup, onion (cut up), brown sugar and sauce together.
Dip your wing ding in the sauce. Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
If you have extra sauce, cook in saucepan until thick.

title: mama jo's barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.

title: clarines pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook real slow.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bet's best pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until real moist; gradually add flour small amounts at a time.
Add in rest of ingredients. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for
1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa together.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Mix well. Add melted butter and milk gradually. Add vanilla and cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat and cool a little before pouring into baked pie shells (which are also cool).
Top with meringue and brown in oven at 375° to 400°.

title: aunt bea's sour cream potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes slightly larger than normal size used.
Mix together all ingredients, except eggs.
Pour 1/2 the ingredients into bowl and layer 1/2 the boiled eggs.
Add remainder of mixture and top with remainder of eggs.
Cover and chill thoroughly, preferably overnight.

title: hermits
directions: Cover raisins with cold water; simmer about 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add raisins and nuts; fold in thoroughly.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pan; cut into 24 squares.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet (use Pam to keep from sticking).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Whip egg white and water lightly with fork.
In another bowl, sift together the sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Stir the pecans in egg white mixture until thoroughly covered.
Add sugar mixture and stir.
Place on flat, greased pan and bake in a 225° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper until cool.

title: apple roll
directions: Cook 5 or 10 minutes.

title: french toast bake
directions: Night before:
Cut entire loaf into 1-inch cubes.
Set aside. In a bowl mix together eggs, honey and milk; set aside.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Evenly layer half of the bread cubes in the dish. Cut the cream cheese bricks into 1-inch cubes and add all to the dish on top of the bread.
Top with the rest of the bread cubes. Pour egg mixture evenly over the whole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: big mama biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Pour milk in, stirring until all flour is moist.
Knead gently and press out to 1/2-inch. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased sheet.
Brush with melted butter. Cook at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sauce for baby back ribs
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan.
Add onion and stir often until onion is limp, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce and simmer, uncovered, until reduced to about 2 1/4 cups, about 30 minutes.

title: delmonico's deviled chicken
directions: Combine the butter, mustard, vinegar, salt and paprika in a small bowl.
Rub the mixture all over the chicken and under the skin without detaching it completely.
Refrigerate, covered, for 4 to 6 hours.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in cranberry juice.
Add pineapple grapefruit and mix well.
Add ginger ale last.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into a loaf pan and cover with sauce.
Cover loosely with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing
directions: Whisk up and store in sealed bottle.
Do not refrigerate!

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place one wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Fill liners 3/4 full. Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Remove from pan when cool. Chill. Top with cherry pie filling. Other toppings such as nuts or chocolate may be used.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: old timey biscuit pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spray pan with Pam and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apples.
Granny Smith apples are good for this recipe.
Put sugar and cinnamon in core.
Wrap apples in pastry.

title: fruited rice
directions: Cook white rice, substituting chicken broth for water.
Cook wild rice.
Combine cooked rices.
Saute onion, apple and pear in butter or margarine, just until soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in apricots and almonds; saute briefly.
Toss rices, fruit mixture, cilantro, salt and pepper.
Place in lightly buttered baking dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: my favorite recipe:  pillsbury cake
directions: Combine cake mix, chocolate instant pudding mix, water, oil and mix.
Mix as directed.
One cup chocolate chips may be stirred in after mixing, if desired.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 55 minutes.
Melt Pillsbury frosting supreme (any flavor) and drizzle over cooled cake.

title: corn relish salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed, salt and pepper in large glass bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except lettuce leaves; toss lightly.
Cover; refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 6 servings.

title: best pesto
directions: Finely grind basil, Romano and Parmesan cheese, pine nuts and minced garlic in food processor. Slowly pour oil in. Season pesto with salt and pepper to taste.
Good with any pasta.

title: punch
directions: Mix together Kool-Aid, water and sugar.
Mix in pineapple juice.
Freeze.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni and add remaining ingredients.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature.
Crumble Bleu cheese and grate sharp Cheddar cheese.
You may use cheese bits in place of sharp cheese if desired.
Mix together then add onion juice, pineapple juice and chopped pimento.
Roll cheese mixture into balls and coat with parsley flakes.
Chill and serve.

title: beef hot links and rotini
directions: In large skillet, combine Hillshire Farm beef hot links, green pepper and onion.
Cook until green pepper and onion are tender-crisp.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to milk.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: mother's molasses sweet bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add melted butter and molasses.
Mix well, adding buttermilk and egg.
Pour in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix well and press in ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: deviled corn(ca 1940's)
directions: Make a sauce of the fat, flour, milk and seasonings.
Add corn, egg (slightly beaten) and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into a baking dish, cover with buttered crumbs or cornflake crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad gaynell's way
directions: Season and cook chicken until tender; cool thoroughly.
Remove bones and chop meat.
Combine chicken, celery, sweet and dill relishes and chopped eggs in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Layer 1/3 of stuffing in the bottom of a 9x12 glass casserole dish.
Top with cream of mushroom and 1/2 of chicken.
Top with another 1/3 of stuffing, then cream of chicken and other half of chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Pour chicken broth over the layers and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and Crisco in bowl.
Take out 1/2 cup of mixture to put on top.
Add egg, molasses, hot water and soda. Pour in a pan, then sprinkle the 1/2 cup of mixture on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oysterette appetizers
directions: Put oysterette crackers in plastic bag.
In pint jar, put oil, Ranch dressing, dill weed, lemon pepper and both salts and shake to thoroughly mix.
Pour over oysterettes and shake several times. Marinate 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!

title: curry-chicken salad
directions: Mix in a large bowl, chicken, grapes, celery and green onion. In a blender mix mayonnaise, milk, chutney and curry powder.
Blend well and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken mixture and stir.
Best made the day before.
Good served with cantaloupe and avocado.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine ingredients in given order. Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cool. Spread with frosting.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Blend well after each one.	Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
(I put flavoring in milk.)

title: irish potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Top off with milk.
Blend. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until completely set.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute broccoli and onion. Add remaining ingredients except mushrooms. Stir and cover until cheese melts. Add mushrooms. Can be made in saucepan with low heat.

title: butter pecan frozen dessert
directions: Beat instant vanilla pudding with 2 cups milk.
Add softened ice cream and brittle pieces.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into 14 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Mix Dream Whip with filling and pour into crust.
Freeze.
Filling should be chilled while assembling crust.

title: mexican hush puppies
directions: Combine
cornmeal, flour, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and milk, stirring
just
until moistened.
Stir in corn, cheese, onion
and peppers.
(Do
not overmix batter.) Drop batter by the tablespoonful into hot oil. Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all at once and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix; chill overnight.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Form into balls; place on foil.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Top with a pecan.
Bake at 400° for 11 minutes.
Do not grease pan.

title: popsicles
directions: Melt gelatin with Kool-Aid in boiling water.
Add sugar and cold water, then freeze.

title: golden potato squares
directions: Peel and shred potatoes (raw).
Place in cold water for 10 minutes; drain good.
Saute onion in butter.
Add milk and simmer. Combine eggs, salt and pepper to potatoes.
Add 1 cup cheese; stir in milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: nancy's famous fudge
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Take off heat.
Add milk in small amounts.
Dump onto wax paper on a cookie sheet.
Wait and let cool some.
Pat with hand into shape desired, making sure it's not too thick.
Let cool completely and cut into small squares.

title: roman holiday
directions: Put onions and garlic with meat; cook until done.
When meat is nearly done, add about 2 tablespoons flour.
Add tomato sauce, diluted (half and half).
Add pepper seasonings, etc.
Parboil macaroni until done.
Put a layer of macaroni in pan; put meat on top of this.
Slice cheese and put on top of meat.
Then add more macaroni, layer of meat, then more cheese.
Add sauce as needed. Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut
up
cabbage in small uniform pieces.
Boil cabbage until tender.
Drain
liquid
from cabbage.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put cabbage in a greased casserole.
Barely cover cabbage with
sweet
milk.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Dot with margarine.	Bake in a 350° oven until crackers are golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, chopped onion, chopped pepper, molasses, catsup to taste and Tabasco to taste.
Place in baking dish and top with bacon strips.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fettuccine and asparagus in parmigiana sauce(low-fat)
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add mushrooms and garlic and saute briefly until mushrooms cook.
Stir in asparagus and set aside.

title: sugarless peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat banana, peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and butter until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Beat well.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: club chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour. Gradually add chicken broth to make a smooth sauce. Cook over low heat until thick. Stirring constantly. Add soup and cayenne pepper. Add chicken, rice, mushrooms, pimentos and onion. Pour into greased 2 quart casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: annie's "squeeze in cafe" chili
directions: Spread buns with mustard (or favorite spread).
Line up in pan with sides.
Fill each bun with frankfurter (slit).
Spoon chili/beans over frankfurters.
Sprinkle generously with corn chips.
Cover with foil and bake until nice and hot at 400° (about 20 minutes).
Very good!

title: potato salad
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add other ingredients, except potatoes and eggs.
Cook until bubbly; remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup onion and 1/4 cup salad dressing.
Pour over potatoes and eggs.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix butter and crumbs.
Press firmly in a 9-inch square pan. Add layer each of coconut and chocolate.
Pour milk over top and add nuts.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Yields 16 squares.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat together the brown sugar, pumpkin, salad oil and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture, stirring until smooth.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes around 7 dozen cookies.

title: oat bran raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Use nonstick spray only on bottom of 12 medium muffin pans or line with cups.
Combine dry ingredients. Add milk, eggs and oil.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups to 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake for 17 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: diabetic pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pour into pie shell. Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: yeast bread(good recipe for a beginner)
directions: Combine water and yeast.
Then melt shortening and cool. Measure flour and set aside.
Add to yeast the shortening, egg (which is room temperature), sugar and salt.
Beat this mixture with the mixer.
Add flour, which has the dry milk added, to the yeast mixture.
Add enough to make dough as thick as the mixer will mix.
Then for about 5 minutes, beat with the mixer.
Mix remaining flour, about 1 cup, in and knead.
Let bread rise. Ready to make into 1 loaf of bread or a batch of cinnamon rolls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all of these ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Then mix 2 cups corn flakes (crushed) with 1/2 cup butter.
Put on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg slightly in large bowl.
Blend in pumpkin, sugar, spices, salt and whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours or overnight.
Soften slightly before serving for nice texture.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Empty pineapple and juice in bowl.
Pour pudding over mix. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well; refrigerate.

title: baboon butter
directions: Mash together peanut butter and banana; add other ingredients. Spread on toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot cheesy potatoes
directions: Add Miracle Whip to chopped Velveeta cheese and onions to red potatoes.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Add bacon about 10 minutes before dish is done.

title: strawberry rousse
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in berries and stir until slightly thick.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Pour over cake pieces in pan.
Chill until firm (overnight).

title: swedish strawberry shortbread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix ingredients together.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly golden.

title: apple roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles. Roll to 1/8-inch thickness on a floured surface. Cut each rectangle into 4 strips. Place 1 apple wedge on each strip. Roll up tightly and place, seam side down, in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the other stick of margarine with the powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat this mixture for 15 minutes at a high speed.
Pour over the graham cracker crust.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil and boil 5 minutes, cool. Add Philadelphia cream cheese and blend.
Add salt and gelatin. Refrigerate until partly set.
Add Dream Whip.
Blend all together and refrigerate.

title: blueberries in maple cream
directions: Thoroughly blend the cream with the maple syrup.
The maple flavor should emerge as a subtle aftertaste.
Divide the berries into 1 cup portions and pour 1/2 cup of the maple cream over each. Serve in your prettiest crystal stemware or dessert dishes.
It is easy and will make a beautiful presentation and ending to your dinner party.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except tomatoes).
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add tomatoes before serving.

title: spinach strata(yields 24 servings)
directions: Cover bottom of a greased steam table pan with bread cubes. Top (in order) with spinach, onions, pimientos, cheese and bread crumbs.
Reserve.

title: hot fudge
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add cream and oleo; cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add vanilla.

title: garlic green beans
directions: Wash green beans, trim ends and remove strings.
Bring water to a boil and add beans.
Cover; reduce heat to medium and add new potatoes to beans.
Cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Saute garlic in butter in a small pan and toss beans and potatoes with mixture.
Serve.

title: beef dip
directions: For a spread, mix all ingredients using mayonnaise as desired.

title: best rolls ever
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco, flour and the dissolved yeast.
Mix thoroughly and cover.
Set in warm place and let rise to full capacity.
Punch down.
Make out rolls and place on Pam sprayed pan.
Brush with oil or butter.
Allow to rise 1 hour or more. Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir in hot milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
(Dash top with nutmeg, if desired.)
Bake in hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to 425° and bake for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Beat with mixer.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in diced zucchini.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Needs no icing.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: country style beef stew
directions: Put the meat, water and onion in slow cooker.
Set on high and cook 2 hours.
Heat the vegetables just to boiling in water to cover.
Drain off water and add to meat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour on high.
Turn cooker to low and simmer for 3 hours.

title: chilled cucumber soup
directions: Put chicken broth and cucumbers in blender.
Set blender on high speed for two minutes.
Then add sour cream.
Blend two more minutes at high speed.
Season with salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce and lemon juice.
Test for flavor; chill throughly before serving. Accompany with 1/2 cup finely diced cucumber as garnish.
Yields four cups.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Mix flour, milk, eggs, salt, steak and seasonings together and leave 1/2 hour.
Season meat and put into well-greased shallow pan or baking dish.
Pour melted oleo over and between cubes of meat. Some cubes should be covered.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve with vegetables while hot.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Grease and flour bundt or tube pan. Cream fats and sugar, add eggs one at a time (cold eggs reduce the rise of the cake), add flavors, then add 7-Up and flour alternately until blended. Bake at 350° one hour and 15 minutes.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Spread the beans on a shallow serving dish.
Mix the sour cream with the taco seasoning mix and spread over the beans.
Top with the cheese, tomatoes and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: batter bread
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in warm milk.
Add beaten eggs to mixture and also butter.
Sift flour and salt and add oats.
Add gradually to liquids.
Spread batter in greased pans and brush with melted butter.
Let rise in pan for 1 hour before baking. Bake at 375° until light brown in color.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one, and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter in pan and pour the rest of batter over this.
Make swirls in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodle and beef casserole
directions: Stir once 1/2 way through.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mango chutney
directions: Put mangoes, onions, ginger, almonds and peppers which have been chopped finely and the rest of the ingredients into a pot and mix well.
Cook for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until mangoes are cooked soft.
Put into jars.

title: spinach-hash pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate with shortening or spray.
Mix onion and milk in small bowl.
Let stand 3 minutes. Spoon corned beef hash into prepared pie plate.
Spread evenly over bottom and sides to form a shell. Spoon spinach over hash. Beat together eggs, milk mixture, salt, pepper and nutmeg in a bowl.
Pour over spinach and mix together lightly. Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until custard is set. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni and add to browned ground beef with green pepper.
Add corn, tomatoes, cheese, olives and pimientos.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: deluxe lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 11 x 19-inch or 12 x 20-inch pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat well.
Blend in the remaining ingredients and mix well by hand.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: nannie's hamburger casserole
directions: Return hamburger back into a large kettle; add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Add drained noodles; top with grated cheese.
Mix butter with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle liberally over top.

title: country fried steak
directions: Batter steak in flour; add to hot grease and cook until brown on both sides.
Take out and put on paper towels.
Pour off part of your grease and add margarine.
Add enough flour to make a thick paste; brown and add enough water to make a thick gravy. Add steak to gravy, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: easy no-bake cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together with mixer.
When thoroughly blended, add the Cool Whip and blend the mixture until it all has the same consistency.
Spread the mixture into the crust.
Now, pour the pie filling over the top.
Chill before serving.

title: very berry cherry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: quick and easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Grease bottom of 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Pour batter into pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool before slicing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Chill, peel and grate into large bowl.
In medium saucepan over low heat, combine butter and cheese, stirring occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes that have been placed in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 8.

title: attitude adjustment recipe
directions: Let anger brew to the simmering point.
Remove from heat before it comes to a boil.
Combine with self-confidence.
Add savvy, determination and purpose and mix energetically with optimism until well blended.
Be careful not to crush, beat or whip into a frenzy or mixture will turn sour.
Top off with a generous helping of the sweetness of life.
Shake yourself vigorously, then let settle. Serves anyone willing to sample it.

title: squash pickle
directions: Bring to a boil; add vegetables and bring to a boil again. Cook 3 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Makes 4 pints.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Make
a paste using two parts of table salt and one part of lemon juice.
Apply the paste to rusted area with a dry cloth and rub.
Mix only what you intend to use in a short time as it will dry out and harden.

title: fire and ice
directions: Mix and chill, covered, 1 hour.
Serve with chips.
Tortillas are best to
me!
Try topped with 1 cup sour cream.

title: different chicken and dressing
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In a large ovenproof fry pan, place butter and melt over medium heat.
Add chicken pieces, 6 at a time, and brown on both sides.
Remove browned chicken from pan and pour off drippings.
In same pan, place sausage, onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook, stirring often, about 5 minutes or until sausage is crumbly and vegetables are tender.
Pour off drippings.
To sausage mixture in pan, add rice, corn and chicken broth.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and arrange chicken on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together sugar and eggs; beat in oil and vanilla.
Stir in apples.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; fold into apple mixture.
Pour into oiled 9-inch square pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt chips, milk and butter. Remove from heat. Add marshmallows and nuts.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch (lined with waxed paper) pan.
Chill for 2 hours.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: warm black bean and spinach salad
directions: Remove large stems from spinach.
Tear spinach into bite size pieces; place into bowl and set aside.
Heat oil in large, nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, green onions and garlic; saute 4 minutes.
Add bell pepper; saute 2 minutes.
Add beans, water, vinegars, salt, red pepper and black pepper; cook for 2 minutes, or until thoroughly heated, stirring frequently. Immediately pour bean mixture over the spinach and toss.
Yields 6 servings.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix well and roll into two logs.
Roll again on crushed pecans and dried parsley.
Place in Saran Wrap or foil.
Place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
May be frozen; eat with crackers.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, bell pepper and onions.
Sprinkle with celery seed.
Heat oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over first mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can be drained or not.

title: hearty macaroni salad
directions: Combine and toss all ingredients except the eggs.
Arrange eggs on top.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon, cloves and water for several minutes. Add tea bags and simmer.
Remove tea bags; add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.
Serve hot.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Measure flour into sifter; add baking powder, salt and sugar. Beat egg and blend in milk.
Add apples, sprinkled with lemon juice.
Sift in dry ingredients and add melted butter.
Beat until just mixed.
Bake on hot griddle.
Serve with melted butter and top with jelly.

title: shredded apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: nova scotia rum cake
directions: Before starting, sample rum to check quality.
If satisfactory, then proceed.
Select large mixing bowl, measuring cup and stop to check rum again.
It must be just right!
To be sure rum is proper quality, pour one level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat as many times as necessary to ensure good quality.
With electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thuger and beat again.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all; simmer 30 minutes.

title: alaska's sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix starter, milk and 1 cup of the flour in a large bowl (the night before if you're serving the biscuits for breakfast; in the morning if you want them for dinner).
Cover and keep at room temperature to rise.
Turn this very soft dough out onto 1 cup flour on a bread board.
Combine salt, sugar, baking powder and soda with remaining 1/2 cup flour and sift over the top of the soft dough.
With hands, mix dry ingredients into soft dough. Knead lightly to get correct consistency.

title: aunt erma's bundt cake
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and
nuts.
Sprinkle half the cinnamon nut mixture into a well-greased 12 cup Bundt pan.
Combine cake and pudding mixes with oil, water or juice, eggs and flavoring in mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed 8 minutes.
Pour half the cake batter into Bundt pan; add remaining nut mixture, then the remaining cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes, then remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Great for breakfast, as a snack or for dessert!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat together the mayonnaise, cream cheese, sugar and cranberry sauce.
Mix in drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Put in loaf pan and freeze.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Pour boiling water into blender container.
Add gelatin and blend at low speed until completely dissolved, about 30 seconds. Add ice cubes and stir until ice is partially melted.
Add strawberries, reserving 6 halves for garnish, if desired, and the whipped topping.
Blend at high speed 30 seconds or until smooth.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut up cucumbers, green pepper and onion.
Put in bowl and add salt and celery seed.
Stir and let set for 1 hour.

title: pelican angel biscuits
directions: Mix soda, sugar and flour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients in warm water together and put on floured board and work adding a little flour until it can be handled.
Pinch off biscuits or roll and cut biscuits, as many as desired.
Put remainder into covered container and keep in refrigerator.	Use as needed.
Will keep several days.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Add the corn to the remaining ingredients.
Add to milk mixture. Stir.
Pour into 8-inch greased casserole and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with hot or mild cheese or tomato sauce.

title: quick sour cream dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a mixing bowl; stir until well blended.
Delicious on
sliced
cucumbers
and
onions or cole slaw.

title: frozen pumpkin squares
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg; stir in pecans.
Combine pumpkin mixture and ice cream in chilled bowl.

title: basic cream pie
directions: Scald 1 1/4 cups milk on stove.
In a separate bowl, beat egg yolks; gradually stir in sugar, then flour, cornstarch, salt and rest of milk.
A little milk can be added along with the flour and cornstarch if it gets too thick.
Stir this into hot milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Let cool a little and pour into pie shell.

title: taco meat
directions: Brown meat. Add onion, tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper, increasing chili powder if needed. Cover and simmer 2 hours. Grate cheese, chop tomatoes and lettuce. Fill taco shells with meat and toppings as desired.

title: chili bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, saute beef until brown. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, then drain.
Stir in tomatoes, beans and seasonings and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in individual molds or one large mold or dish.
Chill until set.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, powder and soda and gradually mix with oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla mixture.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour into well greased and floured tube cake pan.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean when inserted in cake.
Top with Apple Cake Topping.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients well.
Add a little more mayonnaise, if necessary to obtain a good spreading consistency.
Serve with crackers.

title: holiday wreaths
directions: Lightly grease a large sheet of waxed paper and two small spoons.
Melt together margarine and marshmallows; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in cornflakes.
Working quickly with prepared spoons, drop small mounds of cornflake mixture onto waxed paper.
With lightly greased fingers, quickly form cornflake mounds into wreaths with a hole in the center.
Decorate with red-hot candies.
Makes 24 wreaths.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Mix together the flour, pepper and salt.
Coat the cubes of meat thoroughly in the flour and brown in the oil in a large frypan.
As each piece browns, remove from the frypan and put into a crock-pot or Dutch oven.

title: angel icing
directions: Beat egg white in small bowl at medium speed for 2 minutes. Boil sugar, corn syrup and water to hard boil stage or until it forms a thread when poured from spoon.
Pour hot syrup in beaten egg white while beating at high speed.
Combine with egg white (already in stiff peak) until it stands up in peaks.
Add vanilla and mix.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs together by hand.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, zucchini and nuts.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Check after 30 minutes for doneness.
Cool.

title: lemon-herbed chicken
directions: In frypan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, lemon juice, seasonings and crushed marjoram leaves.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender, stirring occasionally.
Garnish chicken with lemon slices. Serve with long grain and wild rice, if desired.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Add noodles to large pan of boiling water.
Boil until tender. Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain oil.
Add sauce and heat. Drain water from noodles.

title: marinara
directions: Saut onions in olive oil until tender. Add garlic, tomatoes, salt and pepper, about 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and about 2 to 3 tablespoons basil. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes. Serve over hot pasta.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Roll cake up again; put on plate.
Cover well and chill.

title: hot russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Store in airtight container.
To prepare, allow 2 heaping teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: coconut pecan icing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pan.
Cook and stir constantly over low heat for about 10 minutes or just until the egg yolk begins to thicken.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and add coconut and pecans.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add flour and mix to make a stiff dough.
Knead thoroughly.
Place in greased bowl and turn, greased side up.
Let rise in warm place 45 minutes.

title: virginia's roast beef au jus
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Place meat, fat side up, in a shallow baking pan.
Put roast in oven and cook for 1 hour.
Turn off heat; do not open door at any time, regardless of length of time the meat has been in oven.
Thirty to forty minutes before serving, turn oven on again to 375°.
Cook meat for 30 to 40 remaining minutes.
Remove roast to serving platter.
Meat will be very brown and crisp on outside.
Carve thin slices.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Prick both sides of steaks with fork and place in large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over steaks.
Cover; marinate 24 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
(Can marinate for 4 to 6 hours and will taste just as good.)
Remove steaks from marinade.
Grill over hot coals 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.
Slice steaks across grain into thin slices.
Good served with a rice casserole.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: low calorie chicken
directions: Mix uncooked rice with chicken broth, pepper and basil.
Chop broccoli and place on rice.
Lay chicken on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs at high speed on electric mixer until thick and lemon colored. Beat in flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, salt and milk.
Using 1 tablespoon per pan, butter and preheat two 9-inch pie pans in hot oven.
Pour batter into pans and arrange apple slices on top.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm with maple syrup or sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.
Serves 4.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, slightly beaten.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake for 45 minutes at 275°.

title: dad's lupini's
directions: Place lupini beans into large pot of water, set aside and soak overnight.
Drain water and refill.
Bring to boil for 10 mins.
Drain water and refill with fresh, cold water.
Let set and then strain and drain water (cleaning both pot and strainer each time, clean water will take residue off) and refill.
I like to do this 4 times a day.
After 4 to 5 days, taste them.
When no longer bitter, they are done.
Add water and salt to jar and cold pack or keep refrigerated.

title: cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together; put in preheated and greased iron skillet.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes one medium size skillet.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper thoroughly, pounding into steak. Brown meat in hot shortening.
Add onion, tomatoes and green pepper; cover.
Cook over low heat in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt bark in microwave.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: french country stew for two
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat in Dutch oven.
Brown drumsticks on both sides.
Add shallots, mushrooms and potato. Pepper lightly.
Pour in white wine or chicken stock.
Cover and lower heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing until blended.
Spoon mixture into small, greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: chipped beef gravy
directions: Chop dried beef.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Blend flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Add dried beef and cook until thickened.

title: mom's scripture cake
directions: Mix well as usual for a cake.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: chocolate wet cake
directions: Mix together in bowl flour and sugar and set aside.
Bring to boil and pour over flour mixture:
margarine, cocoa, oil and water.
Mix together and add buttermilk, cinnamon, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini and onion.
Saute in pan 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots in bowl.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef.
Spray Pam in casserole dish.
Layer ingredients: croutons mixed with butter, zucchini and onion mixture, beef and soup mixture and top with rest of croutons.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Add cool whip to cooked dressing when cool.
Add fruit and stir gently. Cut grapes in half and cube bananas.

title: crescent chicken puffs
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles and seal perforation.
Put 1/2 cup chicken mix on dough.
Roll over and seal or pull up corners together.
Brush with melted oleo.
Dip into crushed croutons or sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Heat soup with a little milk, spoon over puffs.
